3 # Compressed sparse columns data structure
4 # No assumptions about stored zeros in the data structure
5 # Assumes that row values in rowval for each column are sorted
6 # issorted(rowval[colptr[i]:(colptr[i+1]-1)]) == true
7 # Assumes that 1 <= colptr[i] <= colptr[i+1] for i in 1..n
8 # Assumes that nnz <= length(rowval) < typemax(Ti)
9 # Assumes that 0 <= length(nzval) < typemax(Ti)
10
11 """
12 SparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti<:Integer} <: AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}
13
14 Matrix type for storing sparse matrices in the
15 [Compressed Sparse Column](@ref man-csc) format. The standard way
16 of constructing SparseMatrixCSC is through the [`sparse`](@ref) function.
17 See also [`spzeros`](@ref), [`spdiagm`](@ref) and [`sprand`](@ref).
18 """

47 function sparse_check_Ti(m::Integer, n::Integer, Ti::Type)
48 @noinline throwTi(str, lbl, k) =
49 throw(ArgumentError("$str ($lbl = $k) does not fit in Ti = $(Ti)"))
50 0 ≤ m && (!isbitstype(Ti) || m ≤ typemax(Ti)) || throwTi("number of rows", "m", m)
51 0 ≤ n && (!isbitstype(Ti) || n ≤ typemax(Ti)) || throwTi("number of columns", "n", n)
52 end

54 function sparse_check(n::Integer, colptr::Vector{Ti}, rowval, nzval) where Ti
55 # String interpolation is a performance bottleneck when it's part of the same function,
56 # ensure we only do it once committed to the error.
57 throwstart(ckp) = throw(ArgumentError("$ckp == colptr[1] != 1"))
58 throwmonotonic(ckp, ck, k) = throw(ArgumentError("$ckp == colptr[$(k-1)] > colptr[$k] == $ck"))
59
60 sparse_check_length("colptr", colptr, n+1, String) # don't check upper bound
61 ckp = Ti(1)
62 ckp == colptr[1] || throwstart(ckp)
63 @inbounds for k = 2:n+1
64 ck = colptr[k]
65 ckp <= ck || throwmonotonic(ckp, ck, k)
66 ckp = ck
67 end
68 sparse_check_length("rowval", rowval, ckp-1, Ti)
69 sparse_check_length("nzval", nzval, 0, Ti) # we allow empty nzval !!!
70 end
71 function sparse_check_length(rowstr, rowval, minlen, Ti)
72 throwmin(len, minlen, rowstr) = throw(ArgumentError("$len == length($rowstr) < $minlen"))
73 throwmax(len, max, rowstr) = throw(ArgumentError("$len == length($rowstr) >= $max"))
74
75 len = length(rowval)
76 len >= minlen || throwmin(len, minlen, rowstr)
77 !isbitstype(Ti) || len < typemax(Ti) || throwmax(len, typemax(Ti), rowstr)
78 end

92 # Define an alias for views of a SparseMatrixCSC which include all rows and a unit range of the columns.
93 # Also define a union of SparseMatrixCSC and this view since many methods can be defined efficiently for
94 # this union by extracting the fields via the get function: getcolptr, getrowval, and getnzval. The key
95 # insight is that getcolptr on a SparseMatrixCSCView returns an offset view of the colptr of the
96 # underlying SparseMatrixCSC
97 const SparseMatrixCSCView{Tv,Ti} =
98 SubArray{Tv,2,<:AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
99 Tuple{Base.Slice{Base.OneTo{Int}},I}} where {I<:AbstractUnitRange}
100 const SparseMatrixCSCUnion{Tv,Ti} = Union{AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, SparseMatrixCSCView{Tv,Ti}}
101
102 getcolptr(S::SparseMatrixCSC) = getfield(S, :colptr)
103 getcolptr(S::SparseMatrixCSCView) = view(getcolptr(parent(S)), first(axes(S, 2)):(last(axes(S, 2)) + 1))
104 getrowval(S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = rowvals(S)
105 getrowval(S::SparseMatrixCSCView) = rowvals(parent(S))
106 getnzval( S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = nonzeros(S)
107 getnzval( S::SparseMatrixCSCView) = nonzeros(parent(S))
108 nzvalview(S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = view(nonzeros(S), 1:nnz(S))

110 """
111 nnz(A)
112
113 Returns the number of stored (filled) elements in a sparse array.
114
115 # Examples
116 ```jldoctest
117 julia> A = sparse(2I, 3, 3)
118 3×3 SparseMatrixCSC{Int64, Int64} with 3 stored entries:
119 2 ⋅ ⋅
120 ⋅ 2 ⋅
121 ⋅ ⋅ 2
122
123 julia> nnz(A)
124 3
125 ```
126 """
127 nnz(S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = Int(getcolptr(S)[size(S, 2) + 1]) - 1
128 nnz(S::ReshapedArray{<:Any,1,<:AbstractSparseMatrixCSC}) = nnz(parent(S))
129 nnz(S::Adjoint{<:Any,<:AbstractSparseMatrixCSC}) = nnz(parent(S))
130 nnz(S::Transpose{<:Any,<:AbstractSparseMatrixCSC}) = nnz(parent(S))
131 nnz(S::UpperTriangular{<:Any,<:AbstractSparseMatrixCSC}) = nnz1(S)
132 nnz(S::LowerTriangular{<:Any,<:AbstractSparseMatrixCSC}) = nnz1(S)
133 nnz(S::SparseMatrixCSCView) = nnz1(S)
134 nnz1(S) = sum(length.(nzrange.(Ref(S), axes(S, 2))))

136 function count(pred, S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC)
137 count(pred, nzvalview(S)) + pred(zero(eltype(S)))*(prod(size(S)) - nnz(S))

140 """
141 nonzeros(A)
142
143 Return a vector of the structural nonzero values in sparse array `A`. This
144 includes zeros that are explicitly stored in the sparse array. The returned
145 vector points directly to the internal nonzero storage of `A`, and any
146 modifications to the returned vector will mutate `A` as well. See
147 [`rowvals`](@ref) and [`nzrange`](@ref).
148
149 # Examples
150 ```jldoctest
151 julia> A = sparse(2I, 3, 3)
152 3×3 SparseMatrixCSC{Int64, Int64} with 3 stored entries:
153 2 ⋅ ⋅
154 ⋅ 2 ⋅
155 ⋅ ⋅ 2
156
157 julia> nonzeros(A)
158 3-element Vector{Int64}:
159 2
160 2
161 2
162 ```
163 """
164 nonzeros(S::SparseMatrixCSC) = getfield(S, :nzval)
165 nonzeros(S::SparseMatrixCSCView) = nonzeros(S.parent)
166 nonzeros(S::UpperTriangular{<:Any,<:SparseMatrixCSCUnion}) = nonzeros(S.data)
167 nonzeros(S::LowerTriangular{<:Any,<:SparseMatrixCSCUnion}) = nonzeros(S.data)

169 """
170 rowvals(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC)
171
172 Return a vector of the row indices of `A`. Any modifications to the returned
173 vector will mutate `A` as well. Providing access to how the row indices are
174 stored internally can be useful in conjunction with iterating over structural
175 nonzero values. See also [`nonzeros`](@ref) and [`nzrange`](@ref).
176
177 # Examples
178 ```jldoctest
179 julia> A = sparse(2I, 3, 3)
180 3×3 SparseMatrixCSC{Int64, Int64} with 3 stored entries:
181 2 ⋅ ⋅
182 ⋅ 2 ⋅
183 ⋅ ⋅ 2
184
185 julia> rowvals(A)
186 3-element Vector{Int64}:
187 1
188 2
189 3
190 ```
191 """
192 rowvals(S::SparseMatrixCSC) = getfield(S, :rowval)
193 rowvals(S::SparseMatrixCSCView) = rowvals(S.parent)
194 rowvals(S::UpperTriangular{<:Any,<:SparseMatrixCSCUnion}) = rowvals(S.data)
195 rowvals(S::LowerTriangular{<:Any,<:SparseMatrixCSCUnion}) = rowvals(S.data)

197 """
198 nzrange(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, col::Integer)
199
200 Return the range of indices to the structural nonzero values of a sparse matrix
201 column. In conjunction with [`nonzeros`](@ref) and
202 [`rowvals`](@ref), this allows for convenient iterating over a sparse matrix :
203
204 A = sparse(I,J,V)
205 rows = rowvals(A)
206 vals = nonzeros(A)
207 m, n = size(A)
208 for j = 1:n
209 for i in nzrange(A, j)
210 row = rows[i]
211 val = vals[i]
212 # perform sparse wizardry...
213 end
214 end
215 """
216 nzrange(S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, col::Integer) = getcolptr(S)[col]:(getcolptr(S)[col+1]-1)
217 nzrange(S::SparseMatrixCSCView, col::Integer) = nzrange(S.parent, S.indices[2][col])
218 nzrange(S::UpperTriangular{<:Any,<:SparseMatrixCSCUnion}, i::Integer) = nzrangeup(S.data, i)
219 nzrange(S::LowerTriangular{<:Any,<:SparseMatrixCSCUnion}, i::Integer) = nzrangelo(S.data, i)

222 function Base.isstored(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, i::Integer, j::Integer)
223 @boundscheck checkbounds(A, i, j)
224 rows = rowvals(A)
225 for istored in nzrange(A, j) # could do binary search if the row indices are sorted?
226 i == rows[istored] && return true
227 end
228 return false
229 end

273 const brailleBlocks = UInt16['⠁', '⠂', '⠄', '⡀', '⠈', '⠐', '⠠', '⢀']
274 function _show_with_braille_patterns(io::IO, S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSCInclAdjointAndTranspose)
275 m, n = size(S)
276 (m == 0 || n == 0) && return show(io, MIME("text/plain"), S)
277
278 # The maximal number of characters we allow to display the matrix
279 local maxHeight::Int, maxWidth::Int
280 maxHeight = displaysize(io)[1] - 4 # -4 from [Prompt, header, newline after elements, new prompt]
281 maxWidth = displaysize(io)[2] ÷ 2
282
283 # In the process of generating the braille pattern to display the nonzero
284 # structure of `S`, we need to be able to scale the matrix `S` to a
285 # smaller matrix with the same aspect ratio as `S`, but fits on the
286 # available screen space. The size of that smaller matrix is stored
287 # in the variables `scaleHeight` and `scaleWidth`. If no scaling is needed,
288 # we can use the size `m × n` of `S` directly.
289 # We determine if scaling is needed and set the scaling factors
290 # `scaleHeight` and `scaleWidth` accordingly. Note that each available
291 # character can contain up to 4 braille dots in its height (⡇) and up to
292 # 2 braille dots in its width (⠉).
293 if get(io, :limit, true) && (m > 4maxHeight || n > 2maxWidth)
294 s = min(2maxWidth / n, 4maxHeight / m)
295 scaleHeight = floor(Int, s * m)
296 scaleWidth = floor(Int, s * n)
297 else
298 scaleHeight = m
299 scaleWidth = n
300 end
301
302 # `brailleGrid` is used to store the needed braille characters for
303 # the matrix `S`. Each row of the braille pattern to print is stored
304 # in a column of `brailleGrid`.
305 brailleGrid = fill(UInt16(10240), (scaleWidth - 1) ÷ 2 + 2, (scaleHeight - 1) ÷ 4 + 1)
306 brailleGrid[end, :] .= '\n'
307
308 rvals = rowvals(parent(S))
309 rowscale = max(1, scaleHeight - 1) / max(1, m - 1)
310 colscale = max(1, scaleWidth - 1) / max(1, n - 1)
311 if isa(S, AbstractSparseMatrixCSC)
312 @inbounds for j = 1:n
313 # Scale the column index `j` to the best matching column index
314 # of a matrix of size `scaleHeight × scaleWidth`
315 sj = round(Int, (j - 1) * colscale + 1)
316 for x in nzrange(S, j)
317 # Scale the row index `i` to the best matching row index
318 # of a matrix of size `scaleHeight × scaleWidth`
319 si = round(Int, (rvals[x] - 1) * rowscale + 1)
320
321 # Given the index pair `(si, sj)` of the scaled matrix,
322 # calculate the corresponding triple `(k, l, p)` such that the
323 # element at `(si, sj)` can be found at position `(k, l)` in the
324 # braille grid `brailleGrid` and corresponds to the 1-dot braille
325 # character `brailleBlocks[p]`
326 k = (sj - 1) ÷ 2 + 1
327 l = (si - 1) ÷ 4 + 1
328 p = ((sj - 1) % 2) * 4 + ((si - 1) % 4 + 1)
329
330 brailleGrid[k, l] |= brailleBlocks[p]
331 end
332 end
333 else
334 # If `S` is a adjoint or transpose of a sparse matrix we invert the
335 # roles of the indices `i` and `j`
336 @inbounds for i = 1:m
337 si = round(Int, (i - 1) * rowscale + 1)
338 for x in nzrange(parent(S), i)
339 sj = round(Int, (rvals[x] - 1) * colscale + 1)
340 k = (sj - 1) ÷ 2 + 1
341 l = (si - 1) ÷ 4 + 1
342 p = ((sj - 1) % 2) * 4 + ((si - 1) % 4 + 1)
343 brailleGrid[k, l] |= brailleBlocks[p]
344 end
345 end
346 end
347 foreach(c -> print(io, Char(c)), @view brailleGrid[1:end-1])
348 end

352 function sparse_compute_reshaped_colptr_and_rowval!(colptrS::Vector{Ti}, rowvalS::Vector{Ti},
353 mS::Int, nS::Int, colptrA::Vector{Ti},
354 rowvalA::Vector{Ti}, mA::Int, nA::Int) where Ti
355 lrowvalA = length(rowvalA)
356 maxrowvalA = (lrowvalA > 0) ? maximum(rowvalA) : zero(Ti)
357 ((length(colptrA) == (nA+1)) && (maximum(colptrA) <= (lrowvalA+1)) && (maxrowvalA <= mA)) || throw(BoundsError())
358
359 colptrS[1] = 1
360 colA = 1
361 colS = 1
362 ptr = 1
363
364 @inbounds while colA <= nA
365 offsetA = (colA - 1) * mA
366 while ptr <= colptrA[colA+1]-1
367 rowA = rowvalA[ptr]
368 i = offsetA + rowA - 1
369 colSn = div(i, mS) + 1
370 rowS = mod(i, mS) + 1
371 while colS < colSn
372 colptrS[colS+1] = ptr
373 colS += 1
374 end
375 rowvalS[ptr] = rowS
376 ptr += 1
377 end
378 colA += 1
379 end
380 @inbounds while colS <= nS
381 colptrS[colS+1] = ptr
382 colS += 1
383 end
384 end

410 function copyto!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, B::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC)
411 # If the two matrices have the same length then all the
412 # elements in A will be overwritten.
413 if widelength(A) == widelength(B)
414 resize!(nonzeros(A), length(nonzeros(B)))
415 resize!(rowvals(A), length(rowvals(B)))
416 if size(A) == size(B)
417 # Simple case: we can simply copy the internal fields of B to A.
418 copyto!(getcolptr(A), getcolptr(B))
419 copyto!(rowvals(A), rowvals(B))
420 else
421 # This is like a "reshape B into A".
422 sparse_compute_reshaped_colptr_and_rowval!(getcolptr(A), rowvals(A), size(A, 1), size(A, 2), getcolptr(B), rowvals(B), size(B, 1), size(B, 2))
423 end
424 else
425 widelength(A) >= widelength(B) || throw(BoundsError())
426 lB = widelength(B)
427 nnzA = nnz(A)
428 nnzB = nnz(B)
429 # Up to which col, row, and ptr in rowval/nzval will A be overwritten?
430 lastmodcolA = Int(div(lB - 1, size(A, 1))) + 1
431 lastmodrowA = Int(mod(lB - 1, size(A, 1))) + 1
432 lastmodptrA = getcolptr(A)[lastmodcolA]
433 while lastmodptrA < getcolptr(A)[lastmodcolA+1] && rowvals(A)[lastmodptrA] <= lastmodrowA
434 lastmodptrA += 1
435 end
436 lastmodptrA -= 1
437 if lastmodptrA >= nnzB
438 # A will have fewer non-zero elements; unmodified elements are kept at the end.
439 deleteat!(rowvals(A), nnzB+1:lastmodptrA)
440 deleteat!(nonzeros(A), nnzB+1:lastmodptrA)
441 else
442 # A will have more non-zero elements; unmodified elements are kept at the end.
443 resize!(rowvals(A), nnzB + nnzA - lastmodptrA)
444 resize!(nonzeros(A), nnzB + nnzA - lastmodptrA)
445 copyto!(rowvals(A), nnzB+1, rowvals(A), lastmodptrA+1, nnzA-lastmodptrA)
446 copyto!(nonzeros(A), nnzB+1, nonzeros(A), lastmodptrA+1, nnzA-lastmodptrA)
447 end
448 # Adjust colptr accordingly.
449 @inbounds for i in 2:length(getcolptr(A))
450 getcolptr(A)[i] += nnzB - lastmodptrA
451 end
452 sparse_compute_reshaped_colptr_and_rowval!(getcolptr(A), rowvals(A), size(A, 1), lastmodcolA-1, getcolptr(B), rowvals(B), size(B, 1), size(B, 2))
453 end
454 copyto!(nonzeros(A), nonzeros(B))
455 return _checkbuffers(A)
456 end

462 function _sparse_copyto!(dest::AbstractMatrix, src::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC)
463 (dest === src || isempty(src)) && return dest
464 z = convert(eltype(dest), zero(eltype(src))) # should throw if not possible
465 isrc = LinearIndices(src)
466 checkbounds(dest, isrc)
467 # If src is not dense, zero out the portion of dest spanned by isrc
468 if widelength(src) > nnz(src)
469 for i in isrc
470 @inbounds dest[i] = z
471 end
472 end
473 @inbounds for col in axes(src, 2), ptr in nzrange(src, col)
474 row = rowvals(src)[ptr]
475 val = nonzeros(src)[ptr]
476 dest[isrc[row, col]] = val
477 end
478 return dest
479 end
480
481 function copyto!(dest::AbstractMatrix, Rdest::CartesianIndices{2},
482 src::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{T}, Rsrc::CartesianIndices{2}) where {T}
483 isempty(Rdest) && return dest
484 if size(Rdest) != size(Rsrc)
485 throw(ArgumentError("source and destination must have same size (got $(size(Rsrc)) and $(size(Rdest)))"))
486 end
487 checkbounds(dest, Rdest)
488 checkbounds(src, Rsrc)
489 src′ = Base.unalias(dest, src)
490 for I in Rdest
491 @inbounds dest[I] = zero(T) # implicitly convert to eltype(dest), throw if not possible
492 end
493 rows, cols = Rsrc.indices
494 lin = LinearIndices(Base.IdentityUnitRange.(Rsrc.indices))
495 @inbounds for col in cols, ptr in nzrange(src′, col)
496 row = rowvals(src′)[ptr]
497 if row in rows
498 val = nonzeros(src′)[ptr]
499 I = Rdest[lin[row, col]]
500 dest[I] = val
501 end
502 end
503 return dest
504 end

508 # parent method for similar that preserves stored-entry structure (for when new and old dims match)
509 function _sparsesimilar(S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, ::Type{TvNew}, ::Type{TiNew}) where {TvNew,TiNew}
510 newcolptr = copyto!(similar(getcolptr(S), TiNew), getcolptr(S))
511 newrowval = copyto!(similar(rowvals(S), TiNew), rowvals(S))
512 return SparseMatrixCSC(size(S, 1), size(S, 2), newcolptr, newrowval, similar(nonzeros(S), TvNew))
513 end

516 sizehint!(spzeros(TvNew, TiNew, dims...), length(nonzeros(S)))

793 """
794 sparse(I, J, V,[ m, n, combine])
795
796 Create a sparse matrix `S` of dimensions `m x n` such that `S[I[k], J[k]] = V[k]`. The
797 `combine` function is used to combine duplicates. If `m` and `n` are not specified, they
798 are set to `maximum(I)` and `maximum(J)` respectively. If the `combine` function is not
799 supplied, `combine` defaults to `+` unless the elements of `V` are Booleans in which case
800 `combine` defaults to `|`. All elements of `I` must satisfy `1 <= I[k] <= m`, and all
801 elements of `J` must satisfy `1 <= J[k] <= n`. Numerical zeros in (`I`, `J`, `V`) are
802 retained as structural nonzeros; to drop numerical zeros, use [`dropzeros!`](@ref).
803
804 For additional documentation and an expert driver, see `SparseArrays.sparse!`.
805
806 # Examples
807 ```jldoctest
808 julia> Is = [1; 2; 3];
809
810 julia> Js = [1; 2; 3];
811
812 julia> Vs = [1; 2; 3];
813
814 julia> sparse(Is, Js, Vs)
815 3×3 SparseMatrixCSC{Int64, Int64} with 3 stored entries:
816 1 ⋅ ⋅
817 ⋅ 2 ⋅
818 ⋅ ⋅ 3
819 ```
820 """

865 """
866 sparse!(I::AbstractVector{Ti}, J::AbstractVector{Ti}, V::AbstractVector{Tv},
867 m::Integer, n::Integer, combine, klasttouch::Vector{Ti},
868 csrrowptr::Vector{Ti}, csrcolval::Vector{Ti}, csrnzval::Vector{Tv},
869 [csccolptr::Vector{Ti}], [cscrowval::Vector{Ti}, cscnzval::Vector{Tv}] ) where {Tv,Ti<:Integer}
870
871 Parent of and expert driver for [`sparse`](@ref);
872 see [`sparse`](@ref) for basic usage. This method
873 allows the user to provide preallocated storage for `sparse`'s intermediate objects and
874 result as described below. This capability enables more efficient successive construction
875 of [`SparseMatrixCSC`](@ref)s from coordinate representations, and also enables extraction
876 of an unsorted-column representation of the result's transpose at no additional cost.
877
878 This method consists of three major steps: (1) Counting-sort the provided coordinate
879 representation into an unsorted-row CSR form including repeated entries. (2) Sweep through
880 the CSR form, simultaneously calculating the desired CSC form's column-pointer array,
881 detecting repeated entries, and repacking the CSR form with repeated entries combined;
882 this stage yields an unsorted-row CSR form with no repeated entries. (3) Counting-sort the
883 preceding CSR form into a fully-sorted CSC form with no repeated entries.
884
885 Input arrays `csrrowptr`, `csrcolval`, and `csrnzval` constitute storage for the
886 intermediate CSR forms and require `length(csrrowptr) >= m + 1`,
887 `length(csrcolval) >= length(I)`, and `length(csrnzval >= length(I))`. Input
888 array `klasttouch`, workspace for the second stage, requires `length(klasttouch) >= n`.
889 Optional input arrays `csccolptr`, `cscrowval`, and `cscnzval` constitute storage for the
890 returned CSC form `S`. `csccolptr` requires `length(csccolptr) >= n + 1`. If necessary,
891 `cscrowval` and `cscnzval` are automatically resized to satisfy
892 `length(cscrowval) >= nnz(S)` and `length(cscnzval) >= nnz(S)`; hence, if `nnz(S)` is
893 unknown at the outset, passing in empty vectors of the appropriate type (`Vector{Ti}()`
894 and `Vector{Tv}()` respectively) suffices, or calling the `sparse!` method
895 neglecting `cscrowval` and `cscnzval`.
896
897 On return, `csrrowptr`, `csrcolval`, and `csrnzval` contain an unsorted-column
898 representation of the result's transpose.
899
900 You may reuse the input arrays' storage (`I`, `J`, `V`) for the output arrays
901 (`csccolptr`, `cscrowval`, `cscnzval`). For example, you may call
902 `sparse!(I, J, V, csrrowptr, csrcolval, csrnzval, I, J, V)`.
903
904 For the sake of efficiency, this method performs no argument checking beyond
905 `1 <= I[k] <= m` and `1 <= J[k] <= n`. Use with care. Testing with `--check-bounds=yes`
906 is wise.
907
908 This method runs in `O(m, n, length(I))` time. The HALFPERM algorithm described in
909 F. Gustavson, "Two fast algorithms for sparse matrices: multiplication and permuted
910 transposition," ACM TOMS 4(3), 250-269 (1978) inspired this method's use of a pair of
911 counting sorts.
912 """
913 function sparse!(I::AbstractVector{Ti}, J::AbstractVector{Ti},
914 V::AbstractVector{Tv}, m::Integer, n::Integer, combine, klasttouch::Vector{Tj},
915 csrrowptr::Vector{Tj}, csrcolval::Vector{Ti}, csrnzval::Vector{Tv},
916 csccolptr::Vector{Ti}, cscrowval::Vector{Ti}, cscnzval::Vector{Tv}) where {Tv,Ti<:Integer,Tj<:Integer}
917
918 require_one_based_indexing(I, J, V)
919 sparse_check_Ti(m, n, Ti)
920 sparse_check_length("I", I, 0, Tj)
921 # Compute the CSR form's row counts and store them shifted forward by one in csrrowptr
922 fill!(csrrowptr, Tj(0))
923 coolen = length(I)
924 min(length(J), length(V)) >= coolen || throw(ArgumentError("J and V need length >= length(I) = $coolen"))
925 @inbounds for k in 1:coolen
926 Ik = I[k]
927 if 1 > Ik || m < Ik
928 throw(ArgumentError("row indices I[k] must satisfy 1 <= I[k] <= m"))
929 end
930 csrrowptr[Ik+1] += Tj(1)
931 end
932
933 # Compute the CSR form's rowptrs and store them shifted forward by one in csrrowptr
934 countsum = Tj(1)
935 csrrowptr[1] = Tj(1)
936 @inbounds for i in 2:(m+1)
937 overwritten = csrrowptr[i]
938 csrrowptr[i] = countsum
939 countsum += overwritten
940 end
941
942 # Counting-sort the column and nonzero values from J and V into csrcolval and csrnzval
943 # Tracking write positions in csrrowptr corrects the row pointers
944 @inbounds for k in 1:coolen
945 Ik, Jk = I[k], J[k]
946 if Ti(1) > Jk || Ti(n) < Jk
947 throw(ArgumentError("column indices J[k] must satisfy 1 <= J[k] <= n"))
948 end
949 csrk = csrrowptr[Ik+1]
950 @assert csrk >= Tj(1) "index into csrcolval exceeds typemax(Ti)"
951 csrrowptr[Ik+1] = csrk + Tj(1)
952 csrcolval[csrk] = Jk
953 csrnzval[csrk] = V[k]
954 end
955 # This completes the unsorted-row, has-repeats CSR form's construction
956
957 # Sweep through the CSR form, simultaneously (1) calculating the CSC form's column
958 # counts and storing them shifted forward by one in csccolptr; (2) detecting repeated
959 # entries; and (3) repacking the CSR form with the repeated entries combined.
960 #
961 # Minimizing extraneous communication and nonlocality of reference, primarily by using
962 # only a single auxiliary array in this step, is the key to this method's performance.
963 fill!(csccolptr, Ti(0))
964 fill!(klasttouch, Tj(0))
965 writek = Tj(1)
966 newcsrrowptri = Ti(1)
967 origcsrrowptri = Tj(1)
968 origcsrrowptrip1 = csrrowptr[2]
969 @inbounds for i in 1:m
970 for readk in origcsrrowptri:(origcsrrowptrip1-Tj(1))
971 j = csrcolval[readk]
972 if klasttouch[j] < newcsrrowptri
973 klasttouch[j] = writek
974 if writek != readk
975 csrcolval[writek] = j
976 csrnzval[writek] = csrnzval[readk]
977 end
978 writek += Tj(1)
979 csccolptr[j+1] += Ti(1)
980 else
981 klt = klasttouch[j]
982 csrnzval[klt] = combine(csrnzval[klt], csrnzval[readk])
983 end
984 end
985 newcsrrowptri = writek
986 origcsrrowptri = origcsrrowptrip1
987 origcsrrowptrip1 != writek && (csrrowptr[i+1] = writek)
988 i < m && (origcsrrowptrip1 = csrrowptr[i+2])
989 end
990
991 # Compute the CSC form's colptrs and store them shifted forward by one in csccolptr
992 countsum = Tj(1)
993 csccolptr[1] = Ti(1)
994 @inbounds for j in 2:(n+1)
995 overwritten = csccolptr[j]
996 csccolptr[j] = countsum
997 countsum += overwritten
998 Base.hastypemax(Ti) && (countsum <= typemax(Ti) || throw(ArgumentError("more than typemax(Ti)-1 == $(typemax(Ti)-1) entries")))
999 end
1000
1001 # Now knowing the CSC form's entry count, resize cscrowval and cscnzval if necessary
1002 cscnnz = countsum - Tj(1)
1003 length(cscrowval) < cscnnz && resize!(cscrowval, cscnnz)
1004 length(cscnzval) < cscnnz && resize!(cscnzval, cscnnz)
1005
1006 # Finally counting-sort the row and nonzero values from the CSR form into cscrowval and
1007 # cscnzval. Tracking write positions in csccolptr corrects the column pointers.
1008 @inbounds for i in 1:m
1009 for csrk in csrrowptr[i]:(csrrowptr[i+1]-Tj(1))
1010 j = csrcolval[csrk]
1011 x = csrnzval[csrk]
1012 csck = csccolptr[j+1]
1013 csccolptr[j+1] = csck + Ti(1)
1014 cscrowval[csck] = i
1015 cscnzval[csck] = x
1016 end
1017 end
1018
1019 SparseMatrixCSC(m, n, csccolptr, cscrowval, cscnzval)
1020 end

1053 """
1054 halfperm!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{TvA,Ti},
1055 q::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, f::Function = identity) where {Tv,TvA,Ti}
1056
1057 Column-permute and transpose `A`, simultaneously applying `f` to each entry of `A`, storing
1058 the result `(f(A)Q)^T` (`map(f, transpose(A[:,q]))`) in `X`.
1059
1060 Element type `Tv` of `X` must match `f(::TvA)`, where `TvA` is the element type of `A`.
1061 `X`'s dimensions must match those of `transpose(A)` (`size(X, 1) == size(A, 2)` and
1062 `size(X, 2) == size(A, 1)`), and `X` must have enough storage to accommodate all allocated
1063 entries in `A` (`length(rowvals(X)) >= nnz(A)` and `length(nonzeros(X)) >= nnz(A)`).
1064 Column-permutation `q`'s length must match `A`'s column count (`length(q) == size(A, 2)`).
1065
1066 This method is the parent of several methods performing transposition and permutation
1067 operations on [`SparseMatrixCSC`](@ref)s. As this method performs no argument checking,
1068 prefer the safer child methods (`[c]transpose[!]`, `permute[!]`) to direct use.
1069
1070 This method implements the `HALFPERM` algorithm described in F. Gustavson, "Two fast
1071 algorithms for sparse matrices: multiplication and permuted transposition," ACM TOMS 4(3),
1072 250-269 (1978). The algorithm runs in `O(size(A, 1), size(A, 2), nnz(A))` time and requires no space
1073 beyond that passed in.
1074 """
1075 function halfperm!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{TvA,Ti},
1076 q::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, f::Function = identity) where {Tv,TvA,Ti}
1077 _computecolptrs_halfperm!(X, A)
1078 _distributevals_halfperm!(X, A, q, f)
1079 return X
1080 end
1081 """
1082 Helper method for `halfperm!`. Computes `transpose(A[:,q])`'s column pointers, storing them
1083 shifted one position forward in `getcolptr(X)`; `_distributevals_halfperm!` fixes this shift.
1084 """
1085 function _computecolptrs_halfperm!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{TvA,Ti}) where {Tv,TvA,Ti}
1086 # Compute `transpose(A[:,q])`'s column counts. Store shifted forward one position in getcolptr(X).
1087 fill!(getcolptr(X), 0)
1088 @inbounds for k in 1:nnz(A)
1089 getcolptr(X)[rowvals(A)[k] + 1] += 1
1090 end
1091 # Compute `transpose(A[:,q])`'s column pointers. Store shifted forward one position in getcolptr(X).
1092 getcolptr(X)[1] = 1
1093 countsum = 1
1094 @inbounds for k in 2:(size(A, 1) + 1)
1095 overwritten = getcolptr(X)[k]
1096 getcolptr(X)[k] = countsum
1097 countsum += overwritten
1098 end
1099 end
1100 """
1101 Helper method for `halfperm!`. With `transpose(A[:,q])`'s column pointers shifted one
1102 position forward in `getcolptr(X)`, computes `map(f, transpose(A[:,q]))` by appropriately
1103 distributing `rowvals(A)` and `f`-transformed `nonzeros(A)` into `rowvals(X)` and `nonzeros(X)`
1104 respectively. Simultaneously fixes the one-position-forward shift in `getcolptr(X)`.
1105 """
1106 @noinline function _distributevals_halfperm!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
1107 A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{TvA,Ti}, q::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, f::Function) where {Tv,TvA,Ti}
1108 resize!(nonzeros(X), nnz(A))
1109 resize!(rowvals(X), nnz(A))
1110 @inbounds for Xi in 1:size(A, 2)
1111 Aj = q[Xi]
1112 for Ak in nzrange(A, Aj)
1113 Ai = rowvals(A)[Ak]
1114 Xk = getcolptr(X)[Ai + 1]
1115 rowvals(X)[Xk] = Xi
1116 nonzeros(X)[Xk] = f(nonzeros(A)[Ak])
1117 getcolptr(X)[Ai + 1] += 1
1118 end
1119 end
1120 return # kill potential type instability
1121 end
1122
1123 function ftranspose!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, f::Function) where {Tv,Ti}
1124 # Check compatibility of source argument A and destination argument X
1125 if size(X, 2) != size(A, 1)
1126 throw(DimensionMismatch(string("destination argument `X`'s column count, ",
1127 "`size(X, 2) (= $(size(X, 2)))`, must match source argument `A`'s row count, `size(A, 1) (= $(size(A, 1)))`")))
1128 elseif size(X, 1) != size(A, 2)
1129 throw(DimensionMismatch(string("destination argument `X`'s row count, ",
1130 "`size(X, 1) (= $(size(X, 1)))`, must match source argument `A`'s column count, `size(A, 2) (= $(size(A, 2)))`")))
1131 end
1132 halfperm!(X, A, 1:size(A, 2), f)
1133 end
1134 transpose!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}) where {Tv,Ti} = ftranspose!(X, A, identity)
1135 adjoint!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}) where {Tv,Ti} = ftranspose!(X, A, conj)
1136
1137 # manually specifying eltype allows to avoid calling return_type of f on TvA
1138 function ftranspose(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{TvA,Ti}, f::Function, eltype::Type{Tv} = TvA) where {Tv,TvA,Ti}
1139 X = SparseMatrixCSC(size(A, 2), size(A, 1),
1140 ones(Ti, size(A, 1)+1),
1141 Vector{Ti}(undef, 0),
1142 Vector{Tv}(undef, 0))
1143 sizehint!(X, nnz(A))
1144 halfperm!(X, A, 1:size(A, 2), f)
1145 end
1146 adjoint(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = Adjoint(A)
1147 transpose(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = Transpose(A)
1148 Base.copy(A::Adjoint{<:Any,<:AbstractSparseMatrixCSC}) =
1149 ftranspose(A.parent, x -> adjoint(copy(x)), eltype(A))
1150 Base.copy(A::Transpose{<:Any,<:AbstractSparseMatrixCSC}) =
1151 ftranspose(A.parent, x -> transpose(copy(x)), eltype(A))
1152 function Base.permutedims(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, (a,b))
1153 (a, b) == (2, 1) && return ftranspose(A, identity)
1154 (a, b) == (1, 2) && return copy(A)
1155 throw(ArgumentError("no valid permutation of dimensions"))
1156 end

1158 """
1159 unchecked_noalias_permute!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
1160 A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, p::AbstractVector{<:Integer},
1161 q::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, C::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}) where {Tv,Ti}
1162
1163 See [`permute!`](@ref) for basic usage. Parent of `permute[!]`
1164 methods operating on `SparseMatrixCSC`s that assume none of `X`, `A`, and `C` alias each
1165 other. As this method performs no argument checking, prefer the safer child methods
1166 (`permute[!]`) to direct use.
1167
1168 This method consists of two major steps: (1) Column-permute (`Q`,`I[:,q]`) and transpose `A`
1169 to generate intermediate result `(AQ)^T` (`transpose(A[:,q])`) in `C`. (2) Column-permute
1170 (`P^T`, I[:,p]) and transpose intermediate result `(AQ)^T` to generate result
1171 `((AQ)^T P^T)^T = PAQ` (`A[p,q]`) in `X`.
1172
1173 The first step is a call to `halfperm!`, and the second is a variant on `halfperm!` that
1174 avoids an unnecessary length-`nnz(A)` array-sweep and associated recomputation of column
1175 pointers. See [`halfperm!`](:func:SparseArrays.halfperm!) for additional algorithmic
1176 information.
1177
1178 See also `unchecked_aliasing_permute!`.
1179 """
1180 function unchecked_noalias_permute!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
1181 A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, p::AbstractVector{<:Integer},
1182 q::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, C::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}) where {Tv,Ti}
1183 halfperm!(C, A, q)
1184 _computecolptrs_permute!(X, A, q, getcolptr(X))
1185 _distributevals_halfperm!(X, C, p, identity)
1186 return X
1187 end
1188 """
1189 unchecked_aliasing_permute!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
1190 p::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, q::AbstractVector{<:Integer},
1191 C::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, workcolptr::Vector{Ti}) where {Tv,Ti}
1192
1193 See [`permute!`](@ref) for basic usage. Parent of `permute!`
1194 methods operating on [`SparseMatrixCSC`](@ref)s where the source and destination matrices
1195 are the same. See `unchecked_noalias_permute!`
1196 for additional information; these methods are identical but for this method's requirement of
1197 the additional `workcolptr`, `length(workcolptr) >= size(A, 2) + 1`, which enables efficient
1198 handling of the source-destination aliasing.
1199 """
1200 function unchecked_aliasing_permute!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
1201 p::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, q::AbstractVector{<:Integer},
1202 C::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, workcolptr::Vector{Ti}) where {Tv,Ti}
1203 halfperm!(C, A, q)
1204 _computecolptrs_permute!(A, A, q, workcolptr)
1205 _distributevals_halfperm!(A, C, p, identity)
1206 return A
1207 end
1208 """
1209 Helper method for `unchecked_noalias_permute!` and `unchecked_aliasing_permute!`.
1210 Computes `PAQ`'s column pointers, storing them shifted one position forward in `getcolptr(X)`;
1211 `_distributevals_halfperm!` fixes this shift. Saves some work relative to
1212 `_computecolptrs_halfperm!` as described in `uncheckednoalias_permute!`'s documentation.
1213 """
1214 function _computecolptrs_permute!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
1215 A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, q::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, workcolptr::Vector{Ti}) where {Tv,Ti}
1216 # Compute `A[p,q]`'s column counts. Store shifted forward one position in workcolptr.
1217 @inbounds for k in 1:size(A, 2)
1218 workcolptr[k+1] = getcolptr(A)[q[k] + 1] - getcolptr(A)[q[k]]
1219 end
1220 # Compute `A[p,q]`'s column pointers. Store shifted forward one position in getcolptr(X).
1221 getcolptr(X)[1] = 1
1222 countsum = 1
1223 @inbounds for k in 2:(size(X, 2) + 1)
1224 overwritten = workcolptr[k]
1225 getcolptr(X)[k] = countsum
1226 countsum += overwritten
1227 end
1228 end

1230 """
1231 Helper method for `permute` and `permute!` methods operating on `SparseMatrixCSC`s.
1232 Checks compatibility of source argument `A`, row-permutation argument `p`, and
1233 column-permutation argument `q`.
1234 """
1235 function _checkargs_sourcecompatperms_permute!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC,
1236 p::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, q::AbstractVector{<:Integer})
1237 require_one_based_indexing(p, q)
1238 if length(q) != size(A, 2)
1239 throw(DimensionMismatch(string("the length of column-permutation argument `q`, ",
1240 "`length(q) (= $(length(q)))`, must match source argument `A`'s column ",
1241 "count, `size(A, 2) (= $(size(A, 2)))`")))
1242 elseif length(p) != size(A, 1)
1243 throw(DimensionMismatch(string("the length of row-permutation argument `p`, ",
1244 "`length(p) (= $(length(p)))`, must match source argument `A`'s row count, ",
1245 "`size(A, 1) (= $(size(A, 1)))`")))
1246 end
1247 end
1248 """
1249 Helper method for `permute` and `permute!` methods operating on `SparseMatrixCSC`s.
1250 Checks whether row- and column- permutation arguments `p` and `q` are valid permutations.
1251 """
1252 function _checkargs_permutationsvalid_permute!(
1253 p::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, pcheckspace::Vector{Ti},
1254 q::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, qcheckspace::Vector{Ti}) where Ti<:Integer
1255 if !_ispermutationvalid_permute!(p, pcheckspace)
1256 throw(ArgumentError("row-permutation argument `p` must be a valid permutation"))
1257 elseif !_ispermutationvalid_permute!(q, qcheckspace)
1258 throw(ArgumentError("column-permutation argument `q` must be a valid permutation"))
1259 end
1260 end
1261 function _ispermutationvalid_permute!(perm::AbstractVector{<:Integer},
1262 checkspace::Vector{<:Integer})
1263 require_one_based_indexing(perm)
1264 n = length(perm)
1265 checkspace[1:n] .= 0
1266 for k in perm
1267 (0 < k ≤ n) && ((checkspace[k] ⊻= 1) == 1) || return false
1268 end
1269 return true
1270 end

1280 elseif size(X, 2) != size(A, 2)

1287 elseif length(nonzeros(X)) < nnz(A)
1288 throw(ArgumentError(string("the length of destination argument `X`'s `nzval` ",
1289 "array, `length(nonzeros(X)) (= $(length(nonzeros(X))))`, must be greater than or ",
1290 "equal to source argument `A`'s allocated entry count, `nnz(A) (= $(nnz(A)))`")))
1291 end

1299 if size(C, 2) != size(A, 1)
1300 throw(DimensionMismatch(string("intermediate result argument `C`'s column count, ",

1310 throw(ArgumentError(string("the length of intermediate result argument `C`'s ",

1327 """
1328 permute!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
1329 p::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, q::AbstractVector{<:Integer},
1330 [C::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}]) where {Tv,Ti}
1331
1332 Bilaterally permute `A`, storing result `PAQ` (`A[p,q]`) in `X`. Stores intermediate result
1333 `(AQ)^T` (`transpose(A[:,q])`) in optional argument `C` if present. Requires that none of
1334 `X`, `A`, and, if present, `C` alias each other; to store result `PAQ` back into `A`, use
1335 the following method lacking `X`:
1336
1337 permute!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, p::AbstractVector{<:Integer},
1338 q::AbstractVector{<:Integer}[, C::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
1339 [workcolptr::Vector{Ti}]]) where {Tv,Ti}
1340
1341 `X`'s dimensions must match those of `A` (`size(X, 1) == size(A, 1)` and `size(X, 2) == size(A, 2)`), and `X` must
1342 have enough storage to accommodate all allocated entries in `A` (`length(rowvals(X)) >= nnz(A)`
1343 and `length(nonzeros(X)) >= nnz(A)`). Column-permutation `q`'s length must match `A`'s column
1344 count (`length(q) == size(A, 2)`). Row-permutation `p`'s length must match `A`'s row count
1345 (`length(p) == size(A, 1)`).
1346
1347 `C`'s dimensions must match those of `transpose(A)` (`size(C, 1) == size(A, 2)` and `size(C, 2) == size(A, 1)`), and `C`
1348 must have enough storage to accommodate all allocated entries in `A` (`length(rowvals(C)) >= nnz(A)`
1349 and `length(nonzeros(C)) >= nnz(A)`).
1350
1351 For additional (algorithmic) information, and for versions of these methods that forgo
1352 argument checking, see (unexported) parent methods `unchecked_noalias_permute!`
1353 and `unchecked_aliasing_permute!`.
1354
1355 See also [`permute`](@ref).
1356 """
1357 function permute!(X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti},
1358 p::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, q::AbstractVector{<:Integer}) where {Tv,Ti}
1359 _checkargs_sourcecompatdest_permute!(A, X)
1360 _checkargs_sourcecompatperms_permute!(A, p, q)
1361 # bypass strict buffer checking
1362 C = spzeros(Tv, Ti, size(A,2), size(A,1))
1363 resize!(getrowval(C), nnz(A))
1364 resize!(getnzval(C), nnz(A))
1365
1366 _checkargs_permutationsvalid_permute!(p, getcolptr(C), q, getcolptr(X))

1454 ## fkeep! and children tril!, triu!, droptol!, dropzeros[!]
1455
1456 """
1457 fkeep!(A::AbstractSparseArray, f)
1458
1459 Keep elements of `A` for which test `f` returns `true`. `f`'s signature should be
1460
1461 f(i::Integer, [j::Integer,] x) -> Bool
1462
1463 where `i` and `j` are an element's row and column indices and `x` is the element's
1464 value. This method makes a single sweep
1465 through `A`, requiring `O(size(A, 2), nnz(A))`-time for matrices and `O(nnz(A))`-time for vectors
1466 and no space beyond that passed in.
1467
1468 # Examples
1469 ```jldoctest
1470 julia> A = sparse(Diagonal([1, 2, 3, 4]))
1471 4×4 SparseMatrixCSC{Int64, Int64} with 4 stored entries:
1472 1 ⋅ ⋅ ⋅
1473 ⋅ 2 ⋅ ⋅
1474 ⋅ ⋅ 3 ⋅
1475 ⋅ ⋅ ⋅ 4
1476
1477 julia> SparseArrays.fkeep!(A, (i, j, v) -> isodd(v))
1478 4×4 SparseMatrixCSC{Int64, Int64} with 2 stored entries:
1479 1 ⋅ ⋅ ⋅
1480 ⋅ ⋅ ⋅ ⋅
1481 ⋅ ⋅ 3 ⋅
1482 ⋅ ⋅ ⋅ ⋅
1483 ```
1484 """
1485 function fkeep!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, f, trim::Bool = true)
1486 An = size(A, 2)
1487 Acolptr = getcolptr(A)
1488 Arowval = rowvals(A)
1489 Anzval = nonzeros(A)
1490
1491 # Sweep through columns, rewriting kept elements in their new positions
1492 # and updating the column pointers accordingly as we go.
1493 Awritepos = 1
1494 oldAcolptrAj = 1
1495 @inbounds for Aj in 1:An
1496 for Ak in oldAcolptrAj:(Acolptr[Aj+1]-1)
1497 Ai = Arowval[Ak]
1498 Ax = Anzval[Ak]
1499 # If this element should be kept, rewrite in new position
1500 if f(Ai, Aj, Ax)
1501 if Awritepos != Ak
1502 Arowval[Awritepos] = Ai
1503 Anzval[Awritepos] = Ax
1504 end
1505 Awritepos += 1
1506 end
1507 end
1508 oldAcolptrAj = Acolptr[Aj+1]
1509 Acolptr[Aj+1] = Awritepos
1510 end
1511
1512 # Trim A's storage if necessary
1513 Annz = Acolptr[end] - 1
1514 resize!(Arowval, Annz)
1515 resize!(Anzval, Annz)
1516
1517 return A
1518 end
1519
1520 tril!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, k::Integer = 0) =
1521 fkeep!(A, (i, j, x) -> i + k >= j)
1522 triu!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, k::Integer = 0) =
1523 fkeep!(A, (i, j, x) -> j >= i + k)

1529 """
1530 droptol!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, tol) =

1573 function findall(p::Function, S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC)
1574 if p(zero(eltype(S)))
1575 return invoke(findall, Tuple{Function, Any}, p, S)
1576 end
1577
1578 numnz = nnz(S)
1579 inds = Vector{CartesianIndex{2}}(undef, numnz)
1580
1581 count = 0
1582 @inbounds for col = 1 : size(S, 2), k = getcolptr(S)[col] : (getcolptr(S)[col+1]-1)
1583 if p(nonzeros(S)[k])
1584 count += 1
1585 inds[count] = CartesianIndex(rowvals(S)[k], col)
1586 end
1587 end
1588
1589 resize!(inds, count)
1590
1591 return inds
1592 end

1596 function findnz(S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}) where {Tv,Ti}
1597 numnz = nnz(S)
1598 I = Vector{Ti}(undef, numnz)
1599 J = Vector{Ti}(undef, numnz)
1600 V = Vector{Tv}(undef, numnz)
1601
1602 count = 1
1603 @inbounds for col = 1 : size(S, 2), k = getcolptr(S)[col] : (getcolptr(S)[col+1]-1)
1604 I[count] = rowvals(S)[k]
1605 J[count] = col
1606 V[count] = nonzeros(S)[k]
1607 count += 1
1608 end
1609
1610 return (I, J, V)
1611 end

1613 function _sparse_findnextnz(m::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, ij::CartesianIndex{2})
1614 row, col = Tuple(ij)
1615 col > size(m, 2) && return nothing
1616
1617 lo, hi = getcolptr(m)[col], getcolptr(m)[col+1]
1618 n = searchsortedfirst(rowvals(m), row, lo, hi-1, Base.Order.Forward)
1619 if lo <= n <= hi-1
1620 return CartesianIndex(rowvals(m)[n], col)
1621 end
1622 nextcol = searchsortedfirst(getcolptr(m), hi + 1, col + 1, length(getcolptr(m)), Base.Order.Forward)
1623 nextcol > length(getcolptr(m)) && return nothing
1624 nextlo = getcolptr(m)[nextcol-1]
1625 return CartesianIndex(rowvals(m)[nextlo], nextcol - 1)
1626 end
1627
1628 function _sparse_findprevnz(m::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, ij::CartesianIndex{2})
1629 row, col = Tuple(ij)
1630 iszero(col) && return nothing
1631
1632 lo, hi = getcolptr(m)[col], getcolptr(m)[col+1]
1633 n = searchsortedlast(rowvals(m), row, lo, hi-1, Base.Order.Forward)
1634 if lo <= n <= hi-1
1635 return CartesianIndex(rowvals(m)[n], col)
1636 end
1637 prevcol = searchsortedlast(getcolptr(m), lo - 1, 1, col - 1, Base.Order.Forward)
1638 prevcol < 1 && return nothing
1639 prevhi = getcolptr(m)[prevcol+1]
1640 return CartesianIndex(rowvals(m)[prevhi-1], prevcol)
1641 end

1643
1644 function sparse_sortedlinearindices!(I::Vector{Ti}, V::Vector, m::Int, n::Int) where Ti
1645 length(I) == length(V) || throw(ArgumentError("I and V should have the same length"))
1646 nnz = length(V)
1647 colptr = Vector{Ti}(undef, n + 1)
1648 j, colm = 1, 0
1649 @inbounds for col = 1:n+1
1650 colptr[col] = j
1651 while j <= nnz && (I[j] -= colm) <= m
1652 j += 1
1653 end
1654 j <= nnz && (I[j] += colm)
1655 colm += m
1656 end
1657 return SparseMatrixCSC(m, n, colptr, I, V)
1658 end

1660 """
1661 sprand([rng],[type],m,[n],p::AbstractFloat,[rfn])
1662
1663 Create a random length `m` sparse vector or `m` by `n` sparse matrix, in
1664 which the probability of any element being nonzero is independently given by
1665 `p` (and hence the mean density of nonzeros is also exactly `p`). Nonzero
1666 values are sampled from the distribution specified by `rfn` and have the type `type`. The uniform
1667 distribution is used in case `rfn` is not specified. The optional `rng`
1668 argument specifies a random number generator, see [Random Numbers](@ref).
1669
1670 # Examples
1671 ```jldoctest; setup = :(using Random; Random.seed!(1234))
1672 julia> sprand(Bool, 2, 2, 0.5)
1673 2×2 SparseMatrixCSC{Bool, Int64} with 2 stored entries:
1674 1 1
1675 ⋅ ⋅
1676
1677 julia> sprand(Float64, 3, 0.75)
1678 3-element SparseVector{Float64, Int64} with 2 stored entries:
1679 [1] = 0.795547
1680 [2] = 0.49425
1681 ```
1682 """
1683 function sprand(r::AbstractRNG, m::Integer, n::Integer, density::AbstractFloat, rfn::Function, ::Type{T}=eltype(rfn(r, 1))) where T
1684 m, n = Int(m), Int(n)
1685 (m < 0 || n < 0) && throw(ArgumentError("invalid Array dimensions"))
1686 0 <= density <= 1 || throw(ArgumentError("$density not in [0,1]"))
1687 I = randsubseq(r, 1:(m*n), density)
1688 return sparse_sortedlinearindices!(I, convert(Vector{T}, rfn(r,length(I))), m, n)
1689 end

1782 function SparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}(s::UniformScaling, dims::Dims{2}) where {Tv,Ti}
1783 @boundscheck first(dims) < 0 && throw(ArgumentError("first dimension invalid ($(first(dims)) < 0)"))
1784 @boundscheck last(dims) < 0 && throw(ArgumentError("second dimension invalid ($(last(dims)) < 0)"))
1785 iszero(s.λ) && return spzeros(Tv, Ti, dims...)
1786 m, n, k = dims..., min(dims...)
1787 nzval = fill!(Vector{Tv}(undef, k), Tv(s.λ))
1788 rowval = copyto!(Vector{Ti}(undef, k), 1:k)
1789 colptr = copyto!(Vector{Ti}(undef, n + 1), 1:(k + 1))
1790 for i in (k + 2):(n + 1) colptr[i] = (k + 1) end
1791 SparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}(dims..., colptr, rowval, nzval)
1792 end

1796 function Base.isone(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC)
1797 m, n = size(A)
1798 m == n && getcolptr(A)[n+1] >= n+1 || return false
1799 for j in 1:n, k in getcolptr(A)[j]:(getcolptr(A)[j+1] - 1)
1800 i, x = rowvals(A)[k], nonzeros(A)[k]
1801 ifelse(i == j, isone(x), iszero(x)) || return false
1802 end
1803 return true
1804 end

1837 ## full equality
1838 function ==(A1::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, A2::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC)
1839 size(A1) != size(A2) && return false
1840 vals1, vals2 = nonzeros(A1), nonzeros(A2)
1841 rows1, rows2 = rowvals(A1), rowvals(A2)
1842 m, n = size(A1)
1843 @inbounds for i = 1:n
1844 nz1,nz2 = nzrange(A1,i), nzrange(A2,i)
1845 j1,j2 = first(nz1), first(nz2)
1846 # step through the rows of both matrices at once:
1847 while j1 <= last(nz1) && j2 <= last(nz2)
1848 r1,r2 = rows1[j1], rows2[j2]
1849 if r1==r2
1850 vals1[j1]!=vals2[j2] && return false
1851 j1+=1
1852 j2+=1
1853 else
1854 if r1<r2
1855 vals1[j1]!=0 && return false
1856 j1+=1
1857 else
1858 vals2[j2]!=0 && return false
1859 j2+=1
1860 end
1861 end
1862 end
1863 # finish off any left-overs:
1864 for j = j1:last(nz1)
1865 vals1[j]!=0 && return false
1866 end
1867 for j = j2:last(nz2)
1868 vals2[j]!=0 && return false
1869 end
1870 end
1871 return true
1872 end

1877 # and computing reductions along columns into SparseMatrixCSC is
1878 # non-trivial, so use Arrays for output. Array element type is given by `R`.
1879 function Base.reducedim_initarray(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, region, v0, ::Type{R}) where {R}

1883 # General mapreduce
1884 function _mapreducezeros(f, op, ::Type{T}, nzeros::Integer, v0) where T
1885 nzeros == 0 && return v0
1886
1887 # Reduce over first zero
1888 zeroval = f(zero(T))
1889 v = op(v0, zeroval)
1890 isequal(v, v0) && return v
1891
1892 # Reduce over remaining zeros
1893 for i = 2:nzeros
1894 lastv = v
1895 v = op(v, zeroval)
1896 # Bail out early if we reach a fixed point
1897 isequal(v, lastv) && break
1898 end
1899
1900 v
1901 end
1902
1903 function Base._mapreduce(f, op, ::Base.IndexCartesian, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{T}) where T
1904 z = nnz(A)
1905 n = widelength(A)
1906 if z == 0
1907 if n == 0
1908 Base.mapreduce_empty(f, op, T)
1909 else
1910 _mapreducezeros(f, op, T, n-z-1, f(zero(T)))
1911 end
1912 else
1913 _mapreducezeros(f, op, T, n-z, Base._mapreduce(f, op, nzvalview(A)))
1914 end
1915 end
1916
1917 # Specialized mapreduce for +/*/min/max/_extrema_rf
1918 _mapreducezeros(f, op::Union{typeof(Base.add_sum),typeof(+)}, ::Type{T}, nzeros::Integer, v0) where {T} =
1919 nzeros == 0 ? op(zero(v0), v0) : op(f(zero(T))*nzeros, v0)
1920 _mapreducezeros(f, op::Union{typeof(Base.mul_prod),typeof(*)},::Type{T}, nzeros::Integer, v0) where {T} =
1921 nzeros == 0 ? op(one(v0), v0) : op(f(zero(T))^nzeros, v0)
1922 _mapreducezeros(f, op::Union{typeof(min),typeof(max)}, ::Type{T}, nzeros::Integer, v0) where {T} =
1923 nzeros == 0 ? v0 : op(v0, f(zero(T)))
1924 _mapreducezeros(f::Base.ExtremaMap, op::typeof(Base._extrema_rf), ::Type{T}, nzeros::Integer, v0) where {T} =
1925 nzeros == 0 ? v0 : op(v0, f(zero(T)))
1926
1927 function Base._mapreduce(f, op::typeof(*), ::Base.IndexCartesian, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{T}) where T
1928 nzeros = widelength(A)-nnz(A)
1929 if nzeros == 0
1930 # No zeros, so don't compute f(0) since it might throw
1931 Base._mapreduce(f, op, nzvalview(A))
1932 else
1933 v = f(zero(T))^(nzeros)
1934 # Bail out early if initial reduction value is zero
1935 v == zero(T) ? v : v*Base._mapreduce(f, op, nzvalview(A))
1936 end
1937 end

1939 # General mapreducedim
1940 function _mapreducerows!(f, op, R::AbstractArray, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{T}) where T
1941 require_one_based_indexing(A, R)
1942 colptr = getcolptr(A)
1943 rowval = rowvals(A)
1944 nzval = nonzeros(A)
1945 m, n = size(A)
1946 @inbounds for col = 1:n
1947 r = R[1, col]
1948 @simd for j = colptr[col]:colptr[col+1]-1
1949 r = op(r, f(nzval[j]))
1950 end
1951 R[1, col] = _mapreducezeros(f, op, T, m-(colptr[col+1]-colptr[col]), r)
1952 end
1953 R
1954 end
1955
1956 function _mapreducecols!(f, op, R::AbstractArray, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}) where {Tv,Ti}
1957 require_one_based_indexing(A, R)
1958 colptr = getcolptr(A)
1959 rowval = rowvals(A)
1960 nzval = nonzeros(A)
1961 m, n = size(A)
1962 rownz = fill(convert(Ti, n), m)
1963 @inbounds for col = 1:n
1964 @simd for j = colptr[col]:colptr[col+1]-1
1965 row = rowval[j]
1966 R[row, 1] = op(R[row, 1], f(nzval[j]))
1967 rownz[row] -= 1
1968 end
1969 end
1970 @inbounds for i = 1:m
1971 R[i, 1] = _mapreducezeros(f, op, Tv, Int(rownz[i]), R[i, 1])
1972 end
1973 R
1974 end

1976 function Base._mapreducedim!(f, op, R::AbstractArray, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{T}) where T
1977 require_one_based_indexing(A, R)
1978 lsiz = Base.check_reducedims(R,A)
1979 isempty(A) && return R
1980
1981 if size(R, 1) == size(R, 2) == 1
1982 # Reduction along both columns and rows
1983 R[1, 1] = mapreduce(f, op, A)
1984 elseif size(R, 1) == 1
1985 # Reduction along rows
1986 _mapreducerows!(f, op, R, A)
1987 elseif size(R, 2) == 1
1988 # Reduction along columns
1989 _mapreducecols!(f, op, R, A)
1990 else
1991 # Reduction along a dimension > 2
1992 # Compute op(R, f(A))
1993 m, n = size(A)
1994 nzval = nonzeros(A)
1995 if length(nzval) == m*n
1996 # No zeros, so don't compute f(0) since it might throw
1997 for col = 1:n
1998 @simd for row = 1:size(A, 1)
1999 @inbounds R[row, col] = op(R[row, col], f(nzval[(col-1)*m+row]))
2000 end
2001 end
2002 else
2003 colptr = getcolptr(A)
2004 rowval = rowvals(A)
2005 zeroval = f(zero(T))
2006 @inbounds for col = 1:n
2007 lastrow = 0
2008 for j = colptr[col]:colptr[col+1]-1
2009 row = rowval[j]
2010 @simd for i = lastrow+1:row-1 # Zeros before this nonzero
2011 R[i, col] = op(R[i, col], zeroval)
2012 end
2013 R[row, col] = op(R[row, col], f(nzval[j]))
2014 lastrow = row
2015 end
2016 @simd for i = lastrow+1:m # Zeros at end
2017 R[i, col] = op(R[i, col], zeroval)
2018 end
2019 end
2020 end
2021 end
2022 R
2023 end

2025 # Specialized mapreducedim for + cols to avoid allocating a
2026 # temporary array when f(0) == 0
2027 function _mapreducecols!(f, op::typeof(+), R::AbstractArray, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}) where {Tv,Ti}
2028 require_one_based_indexing(A, R)
2029 nzval = nonzeros(A)
2030 m, n = size(A)
2031 if length(nzval) == m*n
2032 # No zeros, so don't compute f(0) since it might throw
2033 for col = 1:n
2034 @simd for row = 1:size(A, 1)
2035 @inbounds R[row, 1] = op(R[row, 1], f(nzval[(col-1)*m+row]))
2036 end
2037 end
2038 else
2039 colptr = getcolptr(A)
2040 rowval = rowvals(A)
2041 zeroval = f(zero(Tv))
2042 if isequal(zeroval, zero(Tv))
2043 # Case where f(0) == 0
2044 @inbounds for col = 1:size(A, 2)
2045 @simd for j = colptr[col]:colptr[col+1]-1
2046 R[rowval[j], 1] += f(nzval[j])
2047 end
2048 end
2049 else
2050 # Case where f(0) != 0
2051 rownz = fill(convert(Ti, n), m)
2052 @inbounds for col = 1:size(A, 2)
2053 @simd for j = colptr[col]:colptr[col+1]-1
2054 row = rowval[j]
2055 R[row, 1] += f(nzval[j])
2056 rownz[row] -= 1
2057 end
2058 end
2059 for i = 1:m
2060 R[i, 1] += rownz[i]*zeroval
2061 end
2062 end
2063 end
2064 R
2065 end

2067 # any(pred, A, dims = 1) => mapreduce(pred, |, A, dims = 1)
2068 # final argument `post` is to allow post-mapping each columnar mapreduce
2069 function _mapreducerows!(pred::P, ::typeof(|), R::AbstractMatrix{Bool}, A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv},
2070 post::F = identity) where {P, F, Tv}
2071 nzval = nonzeros(A)
2072 colptr = getcolptr(A)
2073 m, n = size(A)
2074 @inbounds for ii in 1:n
2075 bi, ei = colptr[ii], colptr[ii+1]
2076 len = ei - bi
2077 # An empty column is trivial
2078 if len == 0
2079 R[1, ii] = post(pred(zero(Tv)))
2080 continue
2081 end
2082 # If predicate on zero is true, then sparse column can be short-circuited
2083 if pred(zero(Tv)) && len < m
2084 R[1, ii] = post(true)
2085 continue
2086 end
2087 # Otherwise reduce over the stored values
2088 r = false
2089 for jj in bi:(ei - 1)
2090 r = pred(nzval[jj])
2091 r && break
2092 end
2093 R[1, ii] = post(r)
2094 end
2095 return R
2096 end
2097 # all(pred, A, dims = 1) => mapreduce(pred, &, A, dims = 1) == .!mapreduce(!pred, |, A, dims = 1)
2098 _mapreducerows!(pred::P, ::typeof(&), R::AbstractMatrix{Bool},
2099 A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) where {P} = _mapreducerows!(!pred, |, R, A, !)

2101 # findmax/min and argmax/min methods
2102 # find first zero value in sparse matrix - return linear index in full matrix
2103 # non-structural zeros are identified by `iszero` in line with the sparse constructors.
2104 function _findz(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, rows=1:size(A, 1), cols=1:size(A, 2)) where {Tv,Ti}
2105 colptr = getcolptr(A); rowval = rowvals(A); nzval = nonzeros(A)
2106 row = 0
2107 rowmin = rows[1]; rowmax = rows[end]
2108 allrows = (rows == 1:size(A, 1))
2109 @inbounds for col in cols
2110 r1::Int = colptr[col]
2111 r2::Int = colptr[col+1] - 1
2112 if !allrows && (r1 <= r2)
2113 r1 = searchsortedfirst(rowval, rowmin, r1, r2, Forward)
2114 (r1 <= r2 ) && (r2 = searchsortedlast(rowval, rowmax, r1, r2, Forward))
2115 end
2116 row = rowmin
2117 while (r1 <= r2) && (row == rowval[r1]) && !iszero(nzval[r1])
2118 r1 += 1
2119 row += 1
2120 end
2121 (row <= rowmax) && (return CartesianIndex(row, col))
2122 end
2123 return CartesianIndex(0, 0)
2124 end

2126 function _findr(op, A, region, Tv)
2127 require_one_based_indexing(A)
2128 Ti = eltype(keys(A))
2129 i1 = first(keys(A))
2130 N = nnz(A)
2131 L = widelength(A)
2132 if L == 0
2133 if prod(map(length, Base.reduced_indices(A, region))) != 0
2134 throw(ArgumentError("array slices must be non-empty"))
2135 else
2136 ri = Base.reduced_indices0(A, region)
2137 return (zeros(Tv, ri), zeros(Ti, ri))
2138 end
2139 end
2140
2141 colptr = getcolptr(A); rowval = rowvals(A); nzval = nonzeros(A); m = size(A, 1); n = size(A, 2)
2142 zval = zero(Tv)
2143 szA = size(A)
2144
2145 if region == 1 || region == (1,)
2146 (N == 0) && (return (fill(zval,1,n), fill(i1,1,n)))
2147 S = Vector{Tv}(undef, n); I = Vector{Ti}(undef, n)
2148 @inbounds for i = 1 : n
2149 Sc = zval; Ic = _findz(A, 1:m, i:i)
2150 if Ic == CartesianIndex(0, 0)
2151 j = colptr[i]
2152 Ic = CartesianIndex(rowval[j], i)
2153 Sc = nzval[j]
2154 end
2155 for j = colptr[i] : colptr[i+1]-1
2156 if op(nzval[j], Sc)
2157 Sc = nzval[j]
2158 Ic = CartesianIndex(rowval[j], i)
2159 end
2160 end
2161 S[i] = Sc; I[i] = Ic
2162 end
2163 return(reshape(S,1,n), reshape(I,1,n))
2164 elseif region == 2 || region == (2,)
2165 (N == 0) && (return (fill(zval,m,1), fill(i1,m,1)))
2166 S = Vector{Tv}(undef, m)
2167 I = Vector{Ti}(undef, m)
2168 @inbounds for row in 1:m
2169 S[row] = zval; I[row] = _findz(A, row:row, 1:n)
2170 if I[row] == CartesianIndex(0, 0)
2171 I[row] = CartesianIndex(row, 1)
2172 S[row] = A[row,1]
2173 end
2174 end
2175 @inbounds for i = 1 : n, j = colptr[i] : colptr[i+1]-1
2176 row = rowval[j]
2177 if op(nzval[j], S[row])
2178 S[row] = nzval[j]
2179 I[row] = CartesianIndex(row, i)
2180 end
2181 end
2182 return (reshape(S,m,1), reshape(I,m,1))
2183 elseif region == (1,2)
2184 (N == 0) && (return (fill(zval,1,1), fill(i1,1,1)))
2185 hasz = nnz(A) != widelength(A)
2186 Sv = hasz ? zval : nzval[1]
2187 Iv::(Ti) = hasz ? _findz(A) : i1
2188 @inbounds for i = 1 : size(A, 2), j = colptr[i] : (colptr[i+1]-1)
2189 if op(nzval[j], Sv)
2190 Sv = nzval[j]
2191 Iv = CartesianIndex(rowval[j], i)
2192 end
2193 end
2194 return (fill(Sv,1,1), fill(Iv,1,1))
2195 else
2196 throw(ArgumentError("invalid value for region; must be 1, 2, or (1,2)"))
2197 end
2198 end

2200 _isless_fm(a, b) = b == b && ( a != a || isless(a, b) )
2201 _isgreater_fm(a, b) = b == b && ( a != a || isless(b, a) )
2202
2203 findmin(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv}, region::Union{Integer,Tuple{Integer},NTuple{2,Integer}}) where {Tv} =
2204 _findr(_isless_fm, A, region, Tv)
2205 findmax(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv}, region::Union{Integer,Tuple{Integer},NTuple{2,Integer}}) where {Tv} =
2206 _findr(_isgreater_fm, A, region, Tv)
2207 findmin(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = (r=findmin(A,(1,2)); (r[1][1], r[2][1]))
2208 findmax(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = (r=findmax(A,(1,2)); (r[1][1], r[2][1]))
2209
2210 argmin(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = findmin(A)[2]
2211 argmax(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = findmax(A)[2]

2214 function rangesearch(haystack::AbstractRange, needle)
2215 (i,rem) = divrem(needle - first(haystack), step(haystack))
2216 (rem==0 && 1<=i+1<=length(haystack)) ? i+1 : 0
2217 end

2221 function getindex(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{T}, i0::Integer, i1::Integer) where T
2222 @boundscheck checkbounds(A, i0, i1)
2223 r1 = Int(getcolptr(A)[i1])
2224 r2 = Int(getcolptr(A)[i1+1]-1)
2225 (r1 > r2) && return zero(T)
2226 r1 = searchsortedfirst(rowvals(A), i0, r1, r2, Forward)
2227 ((r1 > r2) || (rowvals(A)[r1] != i0)) ? zero(T) : nonzeros(A)[r1]
2228 end

2235 function getindex_cols(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, J::AbstractVector) where {Tv,Ti}
2236 require_one_based_indexing(A, J)
2237 # for indexing whole columns
2238 (m, n) = size(A)
2239 nJ = length(J)
2240
2241 colptrA = getcolptr(A); rowvalA = rowvals(A); nzvalA = nonzeros(A)
2242
2243 colptrS = Vector{Ti}(undef, nJ+1)
2244 colptrS[1] = 1
2245 nnzS = 0
2246
2247 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2248 col = J[j]
2249 1 <= col <= n || throw(BoundsError())
2250 nnzS += colptrA[col+1] - colptrA[col]
2251 colptrS[j+1] = nnzS + 1
2252 end
2253
2254 rowvalS = Vector{Ti}(undef, nnzS)
2255 nzvalS = Vector{Tv}(undef, nnzS)
2256 ptrS = 0
2257
2258 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2259 col = J[j]
2260 for k = colptrA[col]:colptrA[col+1]-1
2261 ptrS += 1
2262 rowvalS[ptrS] = rowvalA[k]
2263 nzvalS[ptrS] = nzvalA[k]
2264 end

2272 function getindex(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, I::AbstractRange, J::AbstractVector) where {Tv,Ti<:Integer}
2273 require_one_based_indexing(A, I, J)
2274 # Ranges for indexing rows
2275 (m, n) = size(A)
2276 # whole columns:
2277 if I == 1:m
2278 return getindex_cols(A, J)
2279 end
2280
2281 nI = length(I)
2282 nI == 0 || (minimum(I) >= 1 && maximum(I) <= m) || throw(BoundsError())
2283 nJ = length(J)
2284 colptrA = getcolptr(A); rowvalA = rowvals(A); nzvalA = nonzeros(A)
2285 colptrS = Vector{Ti}(undef, nJ+1)
2286 colptrS[1] = 1
2287 nnzS = 0
2288
2289 # Form the structure of the result and compute space
2290 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2291 col = J[j]
2292 1 <= col <= n || throw(BoundsError())
2293 @simd for k in colptrA[col]:colptrA[col+1]-1
2294 nnzS += rowvalA[k] in I # `in` is fast for ranges
2295 end
2296 colptrS[j+1] = nnzS+1
2297 end
2298
2299 # Populate the values in the result
2300 rowvalS = Vector{Ti}(undef, nnzS)
2301 nzvalS = Vector{Tv}(undef, nnzS)
2302 ptrS = 1
2303
2304 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2305 col = J[j]
2306 for k = getindex_traverse_col(I, colptrA[col], colptrA[col+1]-1)
2307 rowA = rowvalA[k]
2308 i = rangesearch(I, rowA)
2309 if i > 0
2310 rowvalS[ptrS] = i
2311 nzvalS[ptrS] = nzvalA[k]
2312 ptrS += 1
2313 end
2314 end
2315 end
2316
2317 return SparseMatrixCSC(nI, nJ, colptrS, rowvalS, nzvalS)

2320 function getindex_I_sorted(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, I::AbstractVector, J::AbstractVector) where {Tv,Ti}
2321 require_one_based_indexing(A, I, J)
2322 # Sorted vectors for indexing rows.
2323 # Similar to getindex_general but without the transpose trick.
2324 (m, n) = size(A)
2325
2326 nI = length(I)
2327 nzA = nnz(A)
2328 avgM = div(nzA,n)
2329 # Heuristics based on experiments discussed in:
2330 # https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/12860
2331 # https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/12934
2332 alg = ((m > nzA) && (m > nI)) ? 0 :
2333 ((nI - avgM) > 2^8) ? 1 :
2334 ((avgM - nI) > 2^10) ? 0 : 2
2335
2336 (alg == 0) ? getindex_I_sorted_bsearch_A(A, I, J) :
2337 (alg == 1) ? getindex_I_sorted_bsearch_I(A, I, J) :
2338 getindex_I_sorted_linear(A, I, J)
2339 end
2340
2341 function getindex_I_sorted_bsearch_A(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, I::AbstractVector, J::AbstractVector) where {Tv,Ti}
2342 require_one_based_indexing(A, I, J)
2343 nI = length(I)
2344 nJ = length(J)
2345
2346 colptrA = getcolptr(A); rowvalA = rowvals(A); nzvalA = nonzeros(A)
2347 colptrS = Vector{Ti}(undef, nJ+1)
2348 colptrS[1] = 1
2349
2350 ptrS = 1
2351 # determine result size
2352 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2353 col = J[j]
2354 ptrI::Int = 1 # runs through I
2355 ptrA::Int = colptrA[col]
2356 stopA::Int = colptrA[col+1]-1
2357 if ptrA <= stopA
2358 while ptrI <= nI
2359 rowI = I[ptrI]
2360 ptrI += 1
2361 (rowvalA[ptrA] > rowI) && continue
2362 ptrA = searchsortedfirst(rowvalA, rowI, ptrA, stopA, Base.Order.Forward)
2363 (ptrA <= stopA) || break
2364 if rowvalA[ptrA] == rowI
2365 ptrS += 1
2366 end
2367 end
2368 end
2369 colptrS[j+1] = ptrS
2370 end
2371
2372 rowvalS = Vector{Ti}(undef, ptrS-1)
2373 nzvalS = Vector{Tv}(undef, ptrS-1)
2374
2375 # fill the values
2376 ptrS = 1
2377 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2378 col = J[j]
2379 ptrI::Int = 1 # runs through I
2380 ptrA::Int = colptrA[col]
2381 stopA::Int = colptrA[col+1]-1
2382 if ptrA <= stopA
2383 while ptrI <= nI
2384 rowI = I[ptrI]
2385 if rowvalA[ptrA] <= rowI
2386 ptrA = searchsortedfirst(rowvalA, rowI, ptrA, stopA, Base.Order.Forward)
2387 (ptrA <= stopA) || break
2388 if rowvalA[ptrA] == rowI
2389 rowvalS[ptrS] = ptrI
2390 nzvalS[ptrS] = nzvalA[ptrA]
2391 ptrS += 1
2392 end
2393 end
2394 ptrI += 1
2395 end
2396 end
2397 end
2398 return SparseMatrixCSC(nI, nJ, colptrS, rowvalS, nzvalS)
2399 end

2401 function getindex_I_sorted_linear(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, I::AbstractVector, J::AbstractVector) where {Tv,Ti}
2402 require_one_based_indexing(A, I, J)
2403 nI = length(I)
2404 nJ = length(J)
2405
2406 colptrA = getcolptr(A); rowvalA = rowvals(A); nzvalA = nonzeros(A)
2407 colptrS = Vector{Ti}(undef, nJ+1)
2408 colptrS[1] = 1
2409 cacheI = zeros(Int, size(A, 1))
2410
2411 ptrS = 1
2412 # build the cache and determine result size
2413 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2414 col = J[j]
2415 ptrI::Int = 1 # runs through I
2416 ptrA::Int = colptrA[col]
2417 stopA::Int = colptrA[col+1]
2418 while ptrI <= nI && ptrA < stopA
2419 rowA = rowvalA[ptrA]
2420 rowI = I[ptrI]
2421
2422 if rowI > rowA
2423 ptrA += 1
2424 elseif rowI < rowA
2425 ptrI += 1
2426 else
2427 (cacheI[rowA] == 0) && (cacheI[rowA] = ptrI)
2428 ptrS += 1
2429 ptrI += 1
2430 end
2431 end
2432 colptrS[j+1] = ptrS
2433 end
2434
2435 rowvalS = Vector{Ti}(undef, ptrS-1)
2436 nzvalS = Vector{Tv}(undef, ptrS-1)
2437
2438 # fill the values
2439 ptrS = 1
2440 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2441 col = J[j]
2442 ptrA::Int = colptrA[col]
2443 stopA::Int = colptrA[col+1]
2444 while ptrA < stopA
2445 rowA = rowvalA[ptrA]
2446 ptrI = cacheI[rowA]
2447 if ptrI > 0
2448 while ptrI <= nI && I[ptrI] == rowA
2449 rowvalS[ptrS] = ptrI
2450 nzvalS[ptrS] = nzvalA[ptrA]
2451 ptrS += 1
2452 ptrI += 1
2453 end
2454 end
2455 ptrA += 1
2456 end
2457 end
2458 return SparseMatrixCSC(nI, nJ, colptrS, rowvalS, nzvalS)
2459 end

2461 function getindex_I_sorted_bsearch_I(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, I::AbstractVector, J::AbstractVector) where {Tv,Ti}
2462 require_one_based_indexing(A, I, J)
2463 nI = length(I)
2464 nJ = length(J)
2465
2466 colptrA = getcolptr(A); rowvalA = rowvals(A); nzvalA = nonzeros(A)
2467 colptrS = Vector{Ti}(undef, nJ+1)
2468 colptrS[1] = 1
2469
2470 m = size(A, 1)
2471
2472 # cacheI is used first to store num occurrences of each row in columns of interest
2473 # and later to store position of first occurrence of each row in I
2474 cacheI = zeros(Int, m)
2475
2476 # count rows
2477 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2478 col = J[j]
2479 for ptrA in colptrA[col]:(colptrA[col+1]-1)
2480 cacheI[rowvalA[ptrA]] += 1
2481 end
2482 end
2483
2484 # fill cache and count nnz
2485 ptrS::Int = 0
2486 ptrI::Int = 1
2487 @inbounds for j = 1:m
2488 cval = cacheI[j]
2489 (cval == 0) && continue
2490 ptrI = searchsortedfirst(I, j, ptrI, nI, Base.Order.Forward)
2491 cacheI[j] = ptrI
2492 while ptrI <= nI && I[ptrI] == j
2493 ptrS += cval
2494 ptrI += 1
2495 end
2496 if ptrI > nI
2497 @simd for i=(j+1):m; @inbounds cacheI[i]=ptrI; end
2498 break
2499 end
2500 end
2501 rowvalS = Vector{Ti}(undef, ptrS)
2502 nzvalS = Vector{Tv}(undef, ptrS)
2503 colptrS[nJ+1] = ptrS+1
2504
2505 # fill the values
2506 ptrS = 1
2507 @inbounds for j = 1:nJ
2508 col = J[j]
2509 ptrA::Int = colptrA[col]
2510 stopA::Int = colptrA[col+1]
2511 while ptrA < stopA
2512 rowA = rowvalA[ptrA]
2513 ptrI = cacheI[rowA]
2514 (ptrI > nI) && break
2515 if ptrI > 0
2516 while I[ptrI] == rowA
2517 rowvalS[ptrS] = ptrI
2518 nzvalS[ptrS] = nzvalA[ptrA]
2519 ptrS += 1
2520 ptrI += 1
2521 (ptrI > nI) && break
2522 end
2523 end
2524 ptrA += 1
2525 end
2526 colptrS[j+1] = ptrS
2527 end
2528 return SparseMatrixCSC(nI, nJ, colptrS, rowvalS, nzvalS)
2529 end

2531 function permute_rows!(S::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, pI::Vector{Int}) where {Tv,Ti}
2532 (m, n) = size(S)
2533 colptrS = getcolptr(S); rowvalS = rowvals(S); nzvalS = nonzeros(S)
2534 # preallocate temporary sort space
2535 nr = min(nnz(S), m)
2536
2537 rowperm = Vector{Int}(undef, nr)
2538 rowval_temp = Vector{Ti}(undef, nr)
2539 rnzval_temp = Vector{Tv}(undef, nr)
2540 perm = Base.Perm(Base.ord(isless, identity, false, Base.Order.Forward), rowval_temp)
2541
2542 @inbounds for j in 1:n
2543 rowrange = nzrange(S, j)
2544 nr = length(rowrange)
2545 resize!(rowperm, nr)
2546 resize!(rowval_temp, nr)
2547 (nr > 0) || continue
2548 k = 1
2549 for i in rowrange
2550 rowA = rowvalS[i]
2551 rowval_temp[k] = pI[rowA]
2552 rnzval_temp[k] = nzvalS[i]
2553 k += 1
2554 end
2555
2556 if nr <= 16
2557 alg = Base.Sort.InsertionSort
2558 else
2559 alg = Base.Sort.QuickSort
2560 end
2561
2562 # Reset permutation
2563 rowperm .= 1:nr
2564 sort!(rowperm, alg, perm)
2565
2566 k = 1
2567 for i in rowrange
2568 kperm = rowperm[k]
2569 rowvalS[i] = rowval_temp[kperm]
2570 nzvalS[i] = rnzval_temp[kperm]
2571 k += 1
2572 end
2573 end
2574 return _checkbuffers(S)
2575 end

2669 function _setindex_scalar!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, _v, _i::Integer, _j::Integer) where {Tv,Ti<:Integer}
2670 v = convert(Tv, _v)
2671 i = convert(Ti, _i)
2672 j = convert(Ti, _j)
2673 if !((1 <= i <= size(A, 1)) & (1 <= j <= size(A, 2)))
2674 throw(BoundsError(A, (i,j)))
2675 end
2676 coljfirstk = Int(getcolptr(A)[j])
2677 coljlastk = Int(getcolptr(A)[j+1] - 1)
2678 searchk = searchsortedfirst(rowvals(A), i, coljfirstk, coljlastk, Base.Order.Forward)
2679 if searchk <= coljlastk && rowvals(A)[searchk] == i
2680 # Column j contains entry A[i,j]. Update and return
2681 nonzeros(A)[searchk] = v
2682 return A
2683 end
2684 # Column j does not contain entry A[i,j]. If v is nonzero, insert entry A[i,j] = v
2685 # and return. If to the contrary v is zero, then simply return.
2686 if !iszero(v)
2687 nz = getcolptr(A)[size(A, 2)+1]
2688 # throw exception before state is partially modified
2689 !isbitstype(Ti) || nz < typemax(Ti) ||
2690 throw(ArgumentError("nnz(A) going to exceed typemax(Ti) = $(typemax(Ti))"))
2691
2692 # if nnz(A) < length(rowval/nzval): no need to grow rowval and preserve values
2693 _insert!(rowvals(A), searchk, i, nz)
2694 _insert!(nonzeros(A), searchk, v, nz)
2695 @simd for m in (j + 1):(size(A, 2) + 1)
2696 @inbounds getcolptr(A)[m] += Ti(1)
2697 end
2698 end
2699 return A
2700 end

2703 function _insert!(v::Vector, pos::Integer, item, nz::Integer)

2705 insert!(v, pos, item)
2706 else # nz < length(v)
2707 Base.unsafe_copyto!(v, pos+1, v, pos, nz - pos)
2708 v[pos] = item
2709 v

2713 function Base.fill!(V::SubArray{Tv, <:Any, <:AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv}, <:Tuple{Vararg{Union{Integer, AbstractVector{<:Integer}},2}}}, x) where Tv
2714 A = V.parent
2715 I, J = V.indices
2716 if isempty(I) || isempty(J); return A; end
2717 # lt=≤ to check for strict sorting
2718 if !issorted(I, lt=≤); I = sort!(unique(I)); end
2719 if !issorted(J, lt=≤); J = sort!(unique(J)); end
2720 if (I[1] < 1 || I[end] > size(A, 1)) || (J[1] < 1 || J[end] > size(A, 2))
2721 throw(BoundsError(A, (I, J)))
2722 end
2723 if iszero(x)
2724 _spsetz_setindex!(A, I, J)
2725 else
2726 _spsetnz_setindex!(A, convert(Tv, x), I, J)
2727 end
2728 return _checkbuffers(A)
2729 end
2730 """
2731 Helper method for immediately preceding fill! method. For all (i,j) such that i in I and
2732 j in J, assigns zero to A[i,j] if A[i,j] is a presently-stored entry, and otherwise does nothing.
2733 """
2734 function _spsetz_setindex!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC,
2735 I::Union{Integer, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}, J::Union{Integer, AbstractVector{<:Integer}})
2736 require_one_based_indexing(A, I, J)
2737 lengthI = length(I)
2738 for j in J
2739 coljAfirstk = getcolptr(A)[j]
2740 coljAlastk = getcolptr(A)[j+1] - 1
2741 coljAfirstk > coljAlastk && continue
2742 kA = coljAfirstk
2743 kI = 1
2744 entrykArow = rowvals(A)[kA]
2745 entrykIrow = I[kI]
2746 while true
2747 if entrykArow < entrykIrow
2748 kA += 1
2749 kA > coljAlastk && break
2750 entrykArow = rowvals(A)[kA]
2751 elseif entrykArow > entrykIrow
2752 kI += 1
2753 kI > lengthI && break
2754 entrykIrow = I[kI]
2755 else # entrykArow == entrykIrow
2756 nonzeros(A)[kA] = 0
2757 kA += 1
2758 kI += 1
2759 (kA > coljAlastk || kI > lengthI) && break
2760 entrykArow = rowvals(A)[kA]
2761 entrykIrow = I[kI]
2762 end
2763 end
2764 end
2765 end
2766 """
2767 Helper method for immediately preceding fill! method. For all (i,j) such that i in I
2768 and j in J, assigns x to A[i,j] if A[i,j] is a presently-stored entry, and allocates and
2769 assigns x to A[i,j] if A[i,j] is not presently stored.
2770 """
2771 function _spsetnz_setindex!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv}, x::Tv,
2772 I::Union{Integer, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}, J::Union{Integer, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}) where Tv
2773 require_one_based_indexing(A, I, J)
2774 m, n = size(A)
2775 lenI = length(I)
2776
2777 nnzA = nnz(A) + lenI * length(J)
2778
2779 rowvalA = rowval = rowvals(A)
2780 nzvalA = nzval = nonzeros(A)
2781
2782 rowidx = 1
2783 nadd = 0
2784 @inbounds for col in 1:n
2785 rrange = nzrange(A, col)
2786 if nadd > 0
2787 getcolptr(A)[col] = getcolptr(A)[col] + nadd
2788 end
2789
2790 if col in J
2791 if isempty(rrange) # set new vals only
2792 nincl = lenI
2793 if nadd == 0
2794 rowval = copy(rowvalA)
2795 nzval = copy(nzvalA)
2796 resize!(rowvalA, nnzA)
2797 resize!(nzvalA, nnzA)
2798 end
2799 r = rowidx:(rowidx+nincl-1)
2800 rowvalA[r] .= I
2801 for rr in r
2802 nzvalA[rr] = x
2803 end
2804 rowidx += nincl
2805 nadd += nincl
2806 else # set old + new vals
2807 old_ptr = rrange[1]
2808 old_stop = rrange[end]
2809 new_ptr = 1
2810 new_stop = lenI
2811
2812 while true
2813 old_row = rowval[old_ptr]
2814 new_row = I[new_ptr]
2815 if old_row < new_row
2816 rowvalA[rowidx] = old_row
2817 nzvalA[rowidx] = nzval[old_ptr]
2818 rowidx += 1
2819 old_ptr += 1
2820 else
2821 if old_row == new_row
2822 old_ptr += 1
2823 else
2824 if nadd == 0
2825 rowval = copy(rowvalA)
2826 nzval = copy(nzvalA)
2827 resize!(rowvalA, nnzA)
2828 resize!(nzvalA, nnzA)
2829 end
2830 nadd += 1
2831 end
2832 rowvalA[rowidx] = new_row
2833 nzvalA[rowidx] = x
2834 rowidx += 1
2835 new_ptr += 1
2836 end
2837
2838 if old_ptr > old_stop
2839 if new_ptr <= new_stop
2840 if nadd == 0
2841 rowval = copy(rowvalA)
2842 nzval = copy(nzvalA)
2843 resize!(rowvalA, nnzA)
2844 resize!(nzvalA, nnzA)
2845 end
2846 r = rowidx:(rowidx+(new_stop-new_ptr))
2847 rowvalA[r] .= I isa Number ? I : I[new_ptr:new_stop]
2848 for rr in r
2849 nzvalA[rr] = x
2850 end
2851 rowidx += length(r)
2852 nadd += length(r)
2853 end
2854 break
2855 end
2856
2857 if new_ptr > new_stop
2858 nincl = old_stop-old_ptr+1
2859 copyto!(rowvalA, rowidx, rowval, old_ptr, nincl)
2860 copyto!(nzvalA, rowidx, nzval, old_ptr, nincl)
2861 rowidx += nincl
2862 break
2863 end
2864 end
2865 end
2866 elseif !isempty(rrange) # set old vals only
2867 nincl = length(rrange)
2868 copyto!(rowvalA, rowidx, rowval, rrange[1], nincl)
2869 copyto!(nzvalA, rowidx, nzval, rrange[1], nincl)
2870 rowidx += nincl
2871 end
2872 end
2873
2874 if nadd > 0
2875 getcolptr(A)[n+1] = rowidx
2876 deleteat!(rowvalA, rowidx:nnzA)
2877 deleteat!(nzvalA, rowidx:nnzA)
2878 end
2879 return A
2880 end

3517 ## Structure query functions
3518 issymmetric(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = is_hermsym(A, identity)
3519
3520 ishermitian(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC) = is_hermsym(A, conj)
3521
3522 function is_hermsym(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, check::Function)
3523 m, n = size(A)
3524 if m != n; return false; end
3525
3526 colptr = getcolptr(A)
3527 rowval = rowvals(A)
3528 nzval = nonzeros(A)
3529 tracker = copy(getcolptr(A))
3530 for col = 1:size(A, 2)
3531 # `tracker` is updated such that, for symmetric matrices,
3532 # the loop below starts from an element at or below the
3533 # diagonal element of column `col`"
3534 for p = tracker[col]:colptr[col+1]-1
3535 val = nzval[p]
3536 row = rowval[p]
3537
3538 # Ignore stored zeros
3539 if iszero(val)
3540 continue
3541 end
3542
3543 # If the matrix was symmetric we should have updated
3544 # the tracker to start at the diagonal or below. Here
3545 # we are above the diagonal so the matrix can't be symmetric.
3546 if row < col
3547 return false
3548 end
3549
3550 # Diagonal element
3551 if row == col
3552 if val != check(val)
3553 return false
3554 end
3555 else
3556 offset = tracker[row]
3557
3558 # If the matrix is unsymmetric, there might not exist
3559 # a rowval[offset]
3560 if offset > length(rowval)
3561 return false
3562 end
3563
3564 row2 = rowval[offset]
3565
3566 # row2 can be less than col if the tracker didn't
3567 # get updated due to stored zeros in previous elements.
3568 # We therefore "catch up" here while making sure that
3569 # the elements are actually zero.
3570 while row2 < col
3571 if !iszero(nzval[offset])
3572 return false
3573 end
3574 offset += 1
3575 row2 = rowval[offset]
3576 tracker[row] += 1
3577 end
3578
3579 # Non zero A[i,j] exists but A[j,i] does not exist
3580 if row2 > col
3581 return false
3582 end
3583
3584 # A[i,j] and A[j,i] exists
3585 if row2 == col
3586 if val != check(nzval[offset])
3587 return false
3588 end
3589 tracker[row] += 1
3590 end
3591 end
3592 end
3593 end
3594 return true
3595 end

3597 function istriu(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC)
3598 m, n = size(A)
3599 colptr = getcolptr(A)
3600 rowval = rowvals(A)
3601 nzval = nonzeros(A)
3602
3603 for col = 1:min(n, m-1)
3604 l1 = colptr[col+1]-1
3605 for i = 0 : (l1 - colptr[col])
3606 if rowval[l1-i] <= col
3607 break
3608 end
3609 if !iszero(nzval[l1-i])
3610 return false
3611 end
3612 end
3613 end
3614 return true
3615 end

3650
3651 function spdiagm_internal(kv::Pair{<:Integer,<:AbstractVector}...)
3652 ncoeffs = 0
3653 for p in kv
3654 ncoeffs += _nnz(p.second)
3655 end
3656 I = Vector{Int}(undef, ncoeffs)
3657 J = Vector{Int}(undef, ncoeffs)
3658 V = Vector{promote_type(map(x -> eltype(x.second), kv)...)}(undef, ncoeffs)
3659 i = 0
3660 m = 0
3661 n = 0
3662 for p in kv
3663 k = p.first
3664 v = p.second
3665 if k < 0
3666 row = -k
3667 col = 0
3668 elseif k > 0
3669 row = 0
3670 col = k
3671 else
3672 row = 0
3673 col = 0
3674 end
3675 numel = _nnz(v)
3676 r = 1+i:numel+i
3677 I[r], J[r] = _indices(v, row, col)
3678 copyto!(view(V, r), _nzvals(v))
3679 veclen = length(v)
3680 m = max(m, row + veclen)
3681 n = max(n, col + veclen)
3682 i += numel
3683 end
3684 return I, J, V, m, n
3685 end

3687 """
3688 spdiagm(kv::Pair{<:Integer,<:AbstractVector}...)
3689 spdiagm(m::Integer, n::Integer, kv::Pair{<:Integer,<:AbstractVector}...)
3690
3691 Construct a sparse diagonal matrix from `Pair`s of vectors and diagonals.
3692 Each vector `kv.second` will be placed on the `kv.first` diagonal. By
3693 default, the matrix is square and its size is inferred
3694 from `kv`, but a non-square size `m`×`n` (padded with zeros as needed)
3695 can be specified by passing `m,n` as the first arguments.
3696
3697 # Examples
3698 ```jldoctest
3699 julia> spdiagm(-1 => [1,2,3,4], 1 => [4,3,2,1])
3700 5×5 SparseMatrixCSC{Int64, Int64} with 8 stored entries:
3701 ⋅ 4 ⋅ ⋅ ⋅
3702 1 ⋅ 3 ⋅ ⋅
3703 ⋅ 2 ⋅ 2 ⋅
3704 ⋅ ⋅ 3 ⋅ 1
3705 ⋅ ⋅ ⋅ 4 ⋅
3706 ```
3707 """
3708 spdiagm(kv::Pair{<:Integer,<:AbstractVector}...) = _spdiagm(nothing, kv...)
3709 spdiagm(m::Integer, n::Integer, kv::Pair{<:Integer,<:AbstractVector}...) = _spdiagm((Int(m),Int(n)), kv...)
3710
3711 """
3712 spdiagm(v::AbstractVector)
3713 spdiagm(m::Integer, n::Integer, v::AbstractVector)
3714
3715 Construct a sparse matrix with elements of the vector as diagonal elements.
3716 By default (no given `m` and `n`), the matrix is square and its size is given
3717 by `length(v)`, but a non-square size `m`×`n` can be specified by passing `m`
3718 and `n` as the first arguments.
3719
3720 !!! compat "Julia 1.6"
3721 These functions require at least Julia 1.6.
3722
3723 # Examples
3724 ```jldoctest
3725 julia> spdiagm([1,2,3])
3726 3×3 SparseMatrixCSC{Int64, Int64} with 3 stored entries:
3727 1 ⋅ ⋅
3728 ⋅ 2 ⋅
3729 ⋅ ⋅ 3
3730
3731 julia> spdiagm(sparse([1,0,3]))
3732 3×3 SparseMatrixCSC{Int64, Int64} with 2 stored entries:
3733 1 ⋅ ⋅
3734 ⋅ ⋅ ⋅
3735 ⋅ ⋅ 3
3736 ```
3737 """
3738 spdiagm(v::AbstractVector) = _spdiagm(nothing, 0 => v)
3739 spdiagm(m::Integer, n::Integer, v::AbstractVector) = _spdiagm((Int(m), Int(n)), 0 => v)
3740
3741 function _spdiagm(size, kv::Pair{<:Integer,<:AbstractVector}...)
3742 I, J, V, mmax, nmax = spdiagm_internal(kv...)
3743 mnmax = max(mmax, nmax)
3744 m, n = something(size, (mnmax,mnmax))
3745 (m ≥ mmax && n ≥ nmax) || throw(DimensionMismatch("invalid size=$size"))
3746 return sparse(I, J, V, m, n)
3747 end

3749 ## expand a colptr or rowptr into a dense index vector
3750 function expandptr(V::Vector{<:Integer})
3751 if V[1] != 1 throw(ArgumentError("first index must be one")) end
3752 res = similar(V, (Int64(V[end]-1),))
3753 for i in 1:(length(V)-1), j in V[i]:(V[i+1] - 1); res[j] = i end
3754 res
3755 end

3758 function diag(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv,Ti}, d::Integer=0) where {Tv,Ti}
3759 m, n = size(A)
3760 k = Int(d)
3761 l = k < 0 ? min(m+k,n) : min(n-k,m)
3762 r, c = k <= 0 ? (-k, 0) : (0, k) # start row/col -1
3763 ind = Vector{Ti}()
3764 val = Vector{Tv}()
3765 for i in 1:l
3766 r += 1; c += 1
3767 r1 = Int(getcolptr(A)[c])
3768 r2 = Int(getcolptr(A)[c+1]-1)
3769 r1 > r2 && continue
3770 r1 = searchsortedfirst(rowvals(A), r, r1, r2, Forward)
3771 ((r1 > r2) || (rowvals(A)[r1] != r)) && continue
3772 push!(ind, i)
3773 push!(val, nonzeros(A)[r1])
3774 end
3775 return SparseVector{Tv,Ti}(l, ind, val)
3776 end

3778 function tr(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC{Tv}) where Tv
3779 n = checksquare(A)
3780 s = zero(Tv)
3781 for i in 1:n
3782 s += A[i,i]
3783 end
3784 return s
3785 end
