3825 ## circular shift
3826
3827 function circshift!(O::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, (r,c)::Base.DimsInteger{2})
3828 nnz = length(nonzeros(X))
3829
3830 iszero(nnz) && return copy!(O, X)
3831
3832 ##### column shift
3833 c = mod(c, size(X, 2))
3834 if iszero(c)
3835 copy!(O, X)
3836 else
3837 ##### readjust output
3838 resize!(getcolptr(O), size(X, 2) + 1)
3839 resize!(rowvals(O), nnz)
3840 resize!(nonzeros(O), nnz)
3841 getcolptr(O)[size(X, 2) + 1] = nnz + 1
3842
3843 # exchange left and right blocks
3844 nleft = getcolptr(X)[size(X, 2) - c + 1] - 1
3845 nright = nnz - nleft
3846 @inbounds for i=c+1:size(X, 2)
3847 getcolptr(O)[i] = getcolptr(X)[i-c] + nright
3848 end
3849 @inbounds for i=1:c
3850 getcolptr(O)[i] = getcolptr(X)[size(X, 2) - c + i] - nleft
3851 end
3852 # rotate rowval and nzval by the right number of elements
3853 circshift!(rowvals(O), rowvals(X), (nright,))
3854 circshift!(nonzeros(O), nonzeros(X), (nright,))
3855 end
3856 ##### row shift
3857 r = mod(r, size(X, 1))
3858 iszero(r) && return O
3859 @inbounds for i=1:size(O, 2)
3860 subvector_shifter!(rowvals(O), nonzeros(O), getcolptr(O)[i], getcolptr(O)[i+1]-1, size(O, 1), r)
3861 end
3862 return _checkbuffers(O)
3863 end
3864
3865 circshift!(O::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, (r,)::Base.DimsInteger{1}) = circshift!(O, X, (r,0))
3866 circshift!(O::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, X::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, r::Real) = circshift!(O, X, (Integer(r),0))

3868 ## swaprows! / swapcols!
3869 macro swap(a, b)
3870 esc(:(($a, $b) = ($b, $a)))
3871 end
3872
3873 function Base.swapcols!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, i, j)
3874 i == j && return
3875
3876 # For simplicitly, let i denote the smaller of the two columns
3877 j < i && @swap(i, j)
3878
3879 colptr = getcolptr(A)
3880 irow = colptr[i]:(colptr[i+1]-1)
3881 jrow = colptr[j]:(colptr[j+1]-1)
3882
3883 function rangeexchange!(arr, irow, jrow)
3884 if length(irow) == length(jrow)
3885 for (a, b) in zip(irow, jrow)
3886 @inbounds @swap(arr[i], arr[j])
3887 end
3888 return
3889 end
3890 # This is similar to the triple-reverse tricks for
3891 # circshift!, except that we have three ranges here,
3892 # so it ends up being 4 reverse calls (but still
3893 # 2 overall reversals for the memory range). Like
3894 # circshift!, there's also a cycle chasing algorithm
3895 # with optimal memory complexity, but the performance
3896 # tradeoffs against this implementation are non-trivial,
3897 # so let's just do this simple thing for now.
3898 # See https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/42676 for
3899 # discussion of circshift!-like algorithms.
3900 reverse!(@view arr[irow])
3901 reverse!(@view arr[jrow])
3902 reverse!(@view arr[(last(irow)+1):(first(jrow)-1)])
3903 reverse!(@view arr[first(irow):last(jrow)])
3904 end
3905 rangeexchange!(rowvals(A), irow, jrow)
3906 rangeexchange!(nonzeros(A), irow, jrow)
3907
3908 if length(irow) != length(jrow)
3909 @inbounds colptr[i+1:j] .+= length(jrow) - length(irow)
3910 end
3911 return nothing
3912 end
3913
3914 function Base.swaprows!(A::AbstractSparseMatrixCSC, i, j)
3915 # For simplicitly, let i denote the smaller of the two rows
3916 j < i && @swap(i, j)
3917
3918 rows = rowvals(A)
3919 vals = nonzeros(A)
3920 for col = 1:size(A, 2)
3921 rr = nzrange(A, col)
3922 iidx = searchsortedfirst(@view(rows[rr]), i)
3923 has_i = iidx <= length(rr) && rows[rr[iidx]] == i
3924
3925 jrange = has_i ? (iidx:last(rr)) : rr
3926 jidx = searchsortedlast(@view(rows[jrange]), j)
3927 has_j = jidx != 0 && rows[jrange[jidx]] == j
3928
3929 if !has_j && !has_i
3930 # Has neither row - nothing to do
3931 continue
3932 elseif has_i && has_j
3933 # This column had both i and j rows - swap them
3934 @swap(vals[rr[iidx]], vals[jrange[jidx]])
3935 elseif has_i
3936 # Update the rowval and then rotate both nonzeros
3937 # and the remaining rowvals into the correct place
3938 rows[rr[iidx]] = j
3939 jidx == 0 && continue
3940 rotate_range = rr[iidx]:jrange[jidx]
3941 circshift!(@view(vals[rotate_range]), -1)
3942 circshift!(@view(rows[rotate_range]), -1)
3943 else
3944 # Same as i, but in the opposite direction
3945 @assert has_j
3946 rows[jrange[jidx]] = i
3947 iidx > length(rr) && continue
3948 rotate_range = rr[iidx]:jrange[jidx]
3949 circshift!(@view(vals[rotate_range]), 1)
3950 circshift!(@view(rows[rotate_range]), 1)
3951 end
3952 end
3953 return nothing
3954 end
